51static uint32_t getTypeAlignIfRequired(const Type *Ty, const ASTContext &Ctx) {
52 auto TI = Ctx.getTypeInfo(Ty);
53 return TI.AlignIsRequired ? TI.Align : 0;
54}
55
56static uint32_t getTypeAlignIfRequired(QualType Ty, const ASTContext &Ctx) {
57 return getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty.getTypePtr(), Ctx);
58}
59
60static uint32_t getDeclAlignIfRequired(const Decl *D, const ASTContext &Ctx) {
61 return D->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>() ? D->getMaxAlignment() : 0;
62}

64CGDebugInfo::CGDebugInfo(CodeGenModule &CGM)
65 : CGM(CGM), DebugKind(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo()),
66 DebugTypeExtRefs(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugTypeExtRefs),
67 DBuilder(CGM.getModule()) {
68 for (const auto &KV : CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugPrefixMap)
69 DebugPrefixMap[KV.first] = KV.second;
70 CreateCompileUnit();
71}

74 assert(LexicalBlockStack.empty() &&
75 "Region stack mismatch, stack not empty!");

78ApplyDebugLocation::ApplyDebugLocation(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
79 SourceLocation TemporaryLocation)
80 : CGF(&CGF) {
81 init(TemporaryLocation);
82}

84ApplyDebugLocation::ApplyDebugLocation(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
85 bool DefaultToEmpty,
86 SourceLocation TemporaryLocation)
87 : CGF(&CGF) {
88 init(TemporaryLocation, DefaultToEmpty);
89}
90
91void ApplyDebugLocation::init(SourceLocation TemporaryLocation,
92 bool DefaultToEmpty) {
93 auto *DI = CGF->getDebugInfo();
94 if (!DI) {
95 CGF = nullptr;
96 return;
97 }
98
99 OriginalLocation = CGF->Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation();
100
101 if (OriginalLocation && !DI->CGM.getExpressionLocationsEnabled())
102 return;
103
104 if (TemporaryLocation.isValid()) {
105 DI->EmitLocation(CGF->Builder, TemporaryLocation);
106 return;
107 }
108
109 if (DefaultToEmpty) {
110 CGF->Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(llvm::DebugLoc());
111 return;
112 }
113
114 // Construct a location that has a valid scope, but no line info.
115 assert(!DI->LexicalBlockStack.empty());
116 CGF->Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(llvm::DebugLoc::get(
117 0, 0, DI->LexicalBlockStack.back(), DI->getInlinedAt()));
118}
119
120ApplyDebugLocation::ApplyDebugLocation(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *E)
121 : CGF(&CGF) {
122 init(E->getExprLoc());
123}
124
125ApplyDebugLocation::ApplyDebugLocation(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::DebugLoc Loc)
126 : CGF(&CGF) {
127 if (!CGF.getDebugInfo()) {
128 this->CGF = nullptr;
129 return;
130 }
131 OriginalLocation = CGF.Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation();
132 if (Loc)
133 CGF.Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(std::move(Loc));
134}
135
136ApplyDebugLocation::~ApplyDebugLocation() {
137 // Query CGF so the location isn't overwritten when location updates are
138 // temporarily disabled (for C++ default function arguments)
139 if (CGF)
140 CGF->Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(std::move(OriginalLocation));
141}
142
143ApplyInlineDebugLocation::ApplyInlineDebugLocation(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
144 GlobalDecl InlinedFn)
145 : CGF(&CGF) {
146 if (!CGF.getDebugInfo()) {
147 this->CGF = nullptr;
148 return;
149 }
150 auto &DI = *CGF.getDebugInfo();
151 SavedLocation = DI.getLocation();
152 assert((DI.getInlinedAt() ==
153 CGF.Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation()->getInlinedAt()) &&
154 "CGDebugInfo and IRBuilder are out of sync");
155
156 DI.EmitInlineFunctionStart(CGF.Builder, InlinedFn);
157}
158
159ApplyInlineDebugLocation::~ApplyInlineDebugLocation() {
160 if (!CGF)
161 return;
162 auto &DI = *CGF->getDebugInfo();
163 DI.EmitInlineFunctionEnd(CGF->Builder);
164 DI.EmitLocation(CGF->Builder, SavedLocation);
165}

167void CGDebugInfo::setLocation(SourceLocation Loc) {
168 // If the new location isn't valid return.
169 if (Loc.isInvalid())
170 return;
171
172 CurLoc = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager().getExpansionLoc(Loc);
173
174 // If we've changed files in the middle of a lexical scope go ahead
175 // and create a new lexical scope with file node if it's different
176 // from the one in the scope.
177 if (LexicalBlockStack.empty())
178 return;
179
180 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
181 auto *Scope = cast<llvm::DIScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
182 PresumedLoc PCLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(CurLoc);
183 if (PCLoc.isInvalid() || Scope->getFile() == getOrCreateFile(CurLoc))
184 return;
185
186 if (auto *LBF = dyn_cast<llvm::DILexicalBlockFile>(Scope)) {
187 LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
188 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(DBuilder.createLexicalBlockFile(
189 LBF->getScope(), getOrCreateFile(CurLoc)));
190 } else if (isa<llvm::DILexicalBlock>(Scope) ||
191 isa<llvm::DISubprogram>(Scope)) {
192 LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
193 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(
194 DBuilder.createLexicalBlockFile(Scope, getOrCreateFile(CurLoc)));
195 }
196}

198llvm::DIScope *CGDebugInfo::getDeclContextDescriptor(const Decl *D) {
199 llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(D);
200 return getContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(D->getDeclContext()),
201 Mod ? Mod : TheCU);
202}
203
204llvm::DIScope *CGDebugInfo::getContextDescriptor(const Decl *Context,
205 llvm::DIScope *Default) {
206 if (!Context)
207 return Default;
208
209 auto I = RegionMap.find(Context);
210 if (I != RegionMap.end()) {
211 llvm::Metadata *V = I->second;
212 return dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIScope>(V);
213 }
214
215 // Check namespace.
216 if (const auto *NSDecl = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(Context))
217 return getOrCreateNamespace(NSDecl);
218
219 if (const auto *RDecl = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(Context))
220 if (!RDecl->isDependentType())
221 return getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getTypeDeclType(RDecl),
222 TheCU->getFile());
223 return Default;
224}
225
226PrintingPolicy CGDebugInfo::getPrintingPolicy() const {
227 PrintingPolicy PP = CGM.getContext().getPrintingPolicy();
228
229 // If we're emitting codeview, it's important to try to match MSVC's naming so
230 // that visualizers written for MSVC will trigger for our class names. In
231 // particular, we can't have spaces between arguments of standard templates
232 // like basic_string and vector.
233 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)
234 PP.MSVCFormatting = true;
235
236 // Apply -fdebug-prefix-map.
237 PP.RemapFilePaths = true;
238 PP.remapPath = [this](StringRef Path) { return remapDIPath(Path); };
239 return PP;
240}

242StringRef CGDebugInfo::getFunctionName(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
243 assert(FD && "Invalid FunctionDecl!");
244 IdentifierInfo *FII = FD->getIdentifier();
245 FunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *Info =
246 FD->getTemplateSpecializationInfo();
247
248 // Emit the unqualified name in normal operation. LLVM and the debugger can
249 // compute the fully qualified name from the scope chain. If we're only
250 // emitting line table info, there won't be any scope chains, so emit the
251 // fully qualified name here so that stack traces are more accurate.
252 // FIXME: Do this when emitting DWARF as well as when emitting CodeView after
253 // evaluating the size impact.
254 bool UseQualifiedName = DebugKind == codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly &&
255 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView;
256
257 if (!Info && FII && !UseQualifiedName)
258 return FII->getName();
259
260 SmallString<128> NS;
261 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(NS);
262 if (!UseQualifiedName)
263 FD->printName(OS);
264 else
265 FD->printQualifiedName(OS, getPrintingPolicy());
266
267 // Add any template specialization args.
268 if (Info) {
269 const TemplateArgumentList *TArgs = Info->TemplateArguments;
270 printTemplateArgumentList(OS, TArgs->asArray(), getPrintingPolicy());
271 }
272
273 // Copy this name on the side and use its reference.
274 return internString(OS.str());
275}

277StringRef CGDebugInfo::getObjCMethodName(const ObjCMethodDecl *OMD) {
278 SmallString<256> MethodName;
279 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(MethodName);
280 OS << (OMD->isInstanceMethod() ? '-' : '+') << '[';
281 const DeclContext *DC = OMD->getDeclContext();
282 if (const auto *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCImplementationDecl>(DC)) {
283 OS << OID->getName();
284 } else if (const auto *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(DC)) {
285 OS << OID->getName();
286 } else if (const auto *OC = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(DC)) {
287 if (OC->IsClassExtension()) {
288 OS << OC->getClassInterface()->getName();
289 } else {
290 OS << OC->getIdentifier()->getNameStart() << '('
291 << OC->getIdentifier()->getNameStart() << ')';
292 }
293 } else if (const auto *OCD = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(DC)) {
294 OS << OCD->getClassInterface()->getName() << '(' << OCD->getName() << ')';
295 } else if (isa<ObjCProtocolDecl>(DC)) {
296 // We can extract the type of the class from the self pointer.
297 if (ImplicitParamDecl *SelfDecl = OMD->getSelfDecl()) {
298 QualType ClassTy =
299 cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(SelfDecl->getType())->getPointeeType();
300 ClassTy.print(OS, PrintingPolicy(LangOptions()));
301 }
302 }
303 OS << ' ' << OMD->getSelector().getAsString() << ']';
304
305 return internString(OS.str());
306}
307
308StringRef CGDebugInfo::getSelectorName(Selector S) {
309 return internString(S.getAsString());
310}

312StringRef CGDebugInfo::getClassName(const RecordDecl *RD) {
313 if (isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
314 SmallString<128> Name;
315 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Name);
316 RD->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, getPrintingPolicy(),
317 /*Qualified*/ false);
318
319 // Copy this name on the side and use its reference.
320 return internString(Name);
321 }
322
323 // quick optimization to avoid having to intern strings that are already
324 // stored reliably elsewhere
325 if (const IdentifierInfo *II = RD->getIdentifier())
326 return II->getName();
327
328 // The CodeView printer in LLVM wants to see the names of unnamed types: it is
329 // used to reconstruct the fully qualified type names.
330 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView) {
331 if (const TypedefNameDecl *D = RD->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl()) {
332 assert(RD->getDeclContext() == D->getDeclContext() &&
333 "Typedef should not be in another decl context!");
334 assert(D->getDeclName().getAsIdentifierInfo() &&
335 "Typedef was not named!");
336 return D->getDeclName().getAsIdentifierInfo()->getName();
337 }
338
339 if (CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
340 StringRef Name;
341
342 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
343 if (const DeclaratorDecl *DD = Context.getDeclaratorForUnnamedTagDecl(RD))
344 // Anonymous types without a name for linkage purposes have their
345 // declarator mangled in if they have one.
346 Name = DD->getName();
347 else if (const TypedefNameDecl *TND =
348 Context.getTypedefNameForUnnamedTagDecl(RD))
349 // Anonymous types without a name for linkage purposes have their
350 // associate typedef mangled in if they have one.
351 Name = TND->getName();
352
353 if (!Name.empty()) {
354 SmallString<256> UnnamedType("<unnamed-type-");
355 UnnamedType += Name;
356 UnnamedType += '>';
357 return internString(UnnamedType);
358 }
359 }
360 }
361
362 return StringRef();
363}

365Optional<llvm::DIFile::ChecksumKind>
366CGDebugInfo::computeChecksum(FileID FID, SmallString<32> &Checksum) const {
367 Checksum.clear();
368
369 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView &&
370 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion < 5)
371 return None;
372
373 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
374 bool Invalid;
375 const llvm::MemoryBuffer *MemBuffer = SM.getBuffer(FID, &Invalid);
376 if (Invalid)
377 return None;
378
379 llvm::MD5 Hash;
380 llvm::MD5::MD5Result Result;
381
382 Hash.update(MemBuffer->getBuffer());
383 Hash.final(Result);
384
385 Hash.stringifyResult(Result, Checksum);
386 return llvm::DIFile::CSK_MD5;
387}

389Optional<StringRef> CGDebugInfo::getSource(const SourceManager &SM,
390 FileID FID) {
391 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmbedSource)
392 return None;
393
394 bool SourceInvalid = false;
395 StringRef Source = SM.getBufferData(FID, &SourceInvalid);
396
397 if (SourceInvalid)
398 return None;
399
400 return Source;
401}

403llvm::DIFile *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateFile(SourceLocation Loc) {
404 if (!Loc.isValid())
405 // If Location is not valid then use main input file.
406 return TheCU->getFile();
407
408 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
409 PresumedLoc PLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(Loc);
410
411 StringRef FileName = PLoc.getFilename();
412 if (PLoc.isInvalid() || FileName.empty())
413 // If the location is not valid then use main input file.
414 return TheCU->getFile();
415
416 // Cache the results.
417 auto It = DIFileCache.find(FileName.data());
418 if (It != DIFileCache.end()) {
419 // Verify that the information still exists.
420 if (llvm::Metadata *V = It->second)
421 return cast<llvm::DIFile>(V);
422 }
423
424 SmallString<32> Checksum;
425
426 // Compute the checksum if possible. If the location is affected by a #line
427 // directive that refers to a file, PLoc will have an invalid FileID, and we
428 // will correctly get no checksum.
429 Optional<llvm::DIFile::ChecksumKind> CSKind =
430 computeChecksum(PLoc.getFileID(), Checksum);
431 Optional<llvm::DIFile::ChecksumInfo<StringRef>> CSInfo;
432 if (CSKind)
433 CSInfo.emplace(*CSKind, Checksum);
434 return createFile(FileName, CSInfo, getSource(SM, SM.getFileID(Loc)));
435}
436
437llvm::DIFile *
438CGDebugInfo::createFile(StringRef FileName,
439 Optional<llvm::DIFile::ChecksumInfo<StringRef>> CSInfo,
440 Optional<StringRef> Source) {
441 StringRef Dir;
442 StringRef File;
443 std::string RemappedFile = remapDIPath(FileName);
444 std::string CurDir = remapDIPath(getCurrentDirname());
445 SmallString<128> DirBuf;
446 SmallString<128> FileBuf;
447 if (llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(RemappedFile)) {
448 // Strip the common prefix (if it is more than just "/") from current
449 // directory and FileName for a more space-efficient encoding.
450 auto FileIt = llvm::sys::path::begin(RemappedFile);
451 auto FileE = llvm::sys::path::end(RemappedFile);
452 auto CurDirIt = llvm::sys::path::begin(CurDir);
453 auto CurDirE = llvm::sys::path::end(CurDir);
454 for (; CurDirIt != CurDirE && *CurDirIt == *FileIt; ++CurDirIt, ++FileIt)
455 llvm::sys::path::append(DirBuf, *CurDirIt);
456 if (std::distance(llvm::sys::path::begin(CurDir), CurDirIt) == 1) {
457 // Don't strip the common prefix if it is only the root "/"
458 // since that would make LLVM diagnostic locations confusing.
459 Dir = {};
460 File = RemappedFile;
461 } else {
462 for (; FileIt != FileE; ++FileIt)
463 llvm::sys::path::append(FileBuf, *FileIt);
464 Dir = DirBuf;
465 File = FileBuf;
466 }
467 } else {
468 Dir = CurDir;
469 File = RemappedFile;
470 }
471 llvm::DIFile *F = DBuilder.createFile(File, Dir, CSInfo, Source);
472 DIFileCache[FileName.data()].reset(F);
473 return F;
474}
475
476std::string CGDebugInfo::remapDIPath(StringRef Path) const {
477 for (const auto &Entry : DebugPrefixMap)
478 if (Path.startswith(Entry.first))
479 return (Twine(Entry.second) + Path.substr(Entry.first.size())).str();
480 return Path.str();
481}

483unsigned CGDebugInfo::getLineNumber(SourceLocation Loc) {
484 if (Loc.isInvalid() && CurLoc.isInvalid())
485 return 0;
486 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
487 PresumedLoc PLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(Loc.isValid() ? Loc : CurLoc);
488 return PLoc.isValid() ? PLoc.getLine() : 0;
489}
490
491unsigned CGDebugInfo::getColumnNumber(SourceLocation Loc, bool Force) {
492 // We may not want column information at all.
493 if (!Force && !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugColumnInfo)
494 return 0;
495
496 // If the location is invalid then use the current column.
497 if (Loc.isInvalid() && CurLoc.isInvalid())
498 return 0;
499 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
500 PresumedLoc PLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(Loc.isValid() ? Loc : CurLoc);
501 return PLoc.isValid() ? PLoc.getColumn() : 0;
502}
503
504StringRef CGDebugInfo::getCurrentDirname() {
505 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugCompilationDir.empty())
506 return CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugCompilationDir;
507
508 if (!CWDName.empty())
509 return CWDName;
510 SmallString<256> CWD;
511 llvm::sys::fs::current_path(CWD);
512 return CWDName = internString(CWD);
513}
514
515void CGDebugInfo::CreateCompileUnit() {
516 SmallString<32> Checksum;
517 Optional<llvm::DIFile::ChecksumKind> CSKind;
518 Optional<llvm::DIFile::ChecksumInfo<StringRef>> CSInfo;
519
520 // Should we be asking the SourceManager for the main file name, instead of
521 // accepting it as an argument? This just causes the main file name to
522 // mismatch with source locations and create extra lexical scopes or
523 // mismatched debug info (a CU with a DW_AT_file of "-", because that's what
524 // the driver passed, but functions/other things have DW_AT_file of "<stdin>"
525 // because that's what the SourceManager says)
526
527 // Get absolute path name.
528 SourceManager &SM = CGM.getContext().getSourceManager();
529 std::string MainFileName = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().MainFileName;
530 if (MainFileName.empty())
531 MainFileName = "<stdin>";
532
533 // The main file name provided via the "-main-file-name" option contains just
534 // the file name itself with no path information. This file name may have had
535 // a relative path, so we look into the actual file entry for the main
536 // file to determine the real absolute path for the file.
537 std::string MainFileDir;
538 if (const FileEntry *MainFile = SM.getFileEntryForID(SM.getMainFileID())) {
539 MainFileDir = remapDIPath(MainFile->getDir()->getName());
540 if (MainFileDir != ".") {
541 llvm::SmallString<1024> MainFileDirSS(MainFileDir);
542 llvm::sys::path::append(MainFileDirSS, MainFileName);
543 MainFileName = MainFileDirSS.str();
544 }
545 // If the main file name provided is identical to the input file name, and
546 // if the input file is a preprocessed source, use the module name for
547 // debug info. The module name comes from the name specified in the first
548 // linemarker if the input is a preprocessed source.
549 if (MainFile->getName() == MainFileName &&
550 FrontendOptions::getInputKindForExtension(
551 MainFile->getName().rsplit('.').second)
552 .isPreprocessed())
553 MainFileName = CGM.getModule().getName().str();
554
555 CSKind = computeChecksum(SM.getMainFileID(), Checksum);
556 }
557
558 llvm::dwarf::SourceLanguage LangTag;
559 const LangOptions &LO = CGM.getLangOpts();
560 if (LO.CPlusPlus) {
561 if (LO.ObjC)
562 LangTag = llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_ObjC_plus_plus;
563 else
564 LangTag = llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C_plus_plus;
565 } else if (LO.ObjC) {
566 LangTag = llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_ObjC;
567 } else if (LO.RenderScript) {
568 LangTag = llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_GOOGLE_RenderScript;
569 } else if (LO.C99) {
570 LangTag = llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C99;
571 } else {
572 LangTag = llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C89;
573 }
574
575 std::string Producer = getClangFullVersion();
576
577 // Figure out which version of the ObjC runtime we have.
578 unsigned RuntimeVers = 0;
579 if (LO.ObjC)
580 RuntimeVers = LO.ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile() ? 2 : 1;
581
582 llvm::DICompileUnit::DebugEmissionKind EmissionKind;
583 switch (DebugKind) {
584 case codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo:
585 case codegenoptions::LocTrackingOnly:
586 EmissionKind = llvm::DICompileUnit::NoDebug;
587 break;
588 case codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly:
589 EmissionKind = llvm::DICompileUnit::LineTablesOnly;
590 break;
591 case codegenoptions::DebugDirectivesOnly:
592 EmissionKind = llvm::DICompileUnit::DebugDirectivesOnly;
593 break;
594 case codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo:
595 case codegenoptions::FullDebugInfo:
596 EmissionKind = llvm::DICompileUnit::FullDebug;
597 break;
598 }
599
600 uint64_t DwoId = 0;
601 auto &CGOpts = CGM.getCodeGenOpts();
602 // The DIFile used by the CU is distinct from the main source
603 // file. Its directory part specifies what becomes the
604 // DW_AT_comp_dir (the compilation directory), even if the source
605 // file was specified with an absolute path.
606 if (CSKind)
607 CSInfo.emplace(*CSKind, Checksum);
608 llvm::DIFile *CUFile = DBuilder.createFile(
609 remapDIPath(MainFileName), remapDIPath(getCurrentDirname()), CSInfo,
610 getSource(SM, SM.getMainFileID()));
611
612 // Create new compile unit.
613 TheCU = DBuilder.createCompileUnit(
614 LangTag, CUFile, CGOpts.EmitVersionIdentMetadata ? Producer : "",
615 LO.Optimize || CGOpts.PrepareForLTO || CGOpts.PrepareForThinLTO,
616 CGOpts.DwarfDebugFlags, RuntimeVers,
617 (CGOpts.getSplitDwarfMode() != CodeGenOptions::NoFission)
618 ? ""
619 : CGOpts.SplitDwarfFile,
620 EmissionKind, DwoId, CGOpts.SplitDwarfInlining,
621 CGOpts.DebugInfoForProfiling,
622 CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isNVPTX()
623 ? llvm::DICompileUnit::DebugNameTableKind::None
624 : static_cast<llvm::DICompileUnit::DebugNameTableKind>(
625 CGOpts.DebugNameTable),
626 CGOpts.DebugRangesBaseAddress);
627}

629llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const BuiltinType *BT) {
630 llvm::dwarf::TypeKind Encoding;
631 StringRef BTName;
632 switch (BT->getKind()) {
633#define BUILTIN_TYPE(Id, SingletonId)
634#define PLACEHOLDER_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
635#include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
636 case BuiltinType::Dependent:
637 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected builtin type");
638 case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
639 return DBuilder.createNullPtrType();
640 case BuiltinType::Void:
641 return nullptr;
642 case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
643 if (!ClassTy)
644 ClassTy =
645 DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type,
646 "objc_class", TheCU, TheCU->getFile(), 0);
647 return ClassTy;
648 case BuiltinType::ObjCId: {
649 // typedef struct objc_class *Class;
650 // typedef struct objc_object {
651 // Class isa;
652 // } *id;
653
654 if (ObjTy)
655 return ObjTy;
656
657 if (!ClassTy)
658 ClassTy =
659 DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type,
660 "objc_class", TheCU, TheCU->getFile(), 0);
661
662 unsigned Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
663
664 auto *ISATy = DBuilder.createPointerType(ClassTy, Size);
665
666 ObjTy = DBuilder.createStructType(TheCU, "objc_object", TheCU->getFile(), 0,
667 0, 0, llvm::DINode::FlagZero, nullptr,
668 llvm::DINodeArray());
669
670 DBuilder.replaceArrays(
671 ObjTy, DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(&*DBuilder.createMemberType(
672 ObjTy, "isa", TheCU->getFile(), 0, Size, 0, 0,
673 llvm::DINode::FlagZero, ISATy)));
674 return ObjTy;
675 }
676 case BuiltinType::ObjCSel: {
677 if (!SelTy)
678 SelTy = DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type,
679 "objc_selector", TheCU,
680 TheCU->getFile(), 0);
681 return SelTy;
682 }
683
684#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
685 case BuiltinType::Id: \
686 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_" #ImgType "_" #Suffix "_t", \
687 SingletonId);
688#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
689 case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
690 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_sampler_t", OCLSamplerDITy);
691 case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
692 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_event_t", OCLEventDITy);
693 case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
694 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_clk_event_t", OCLClkEventDITy);
695 case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
696 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_queue_t", OCLQueueDITy);
697 case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
698 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_reserve_id_t", OCLReserveIDDITy);
699#define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
700 case BuiltinType::Id: \
701 return getOrCreateStructPtrType("opencl_" #ExtType, Id##Ty);
702#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
703
704 case BuiltinType::UChar:
705 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
706 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_unsigned_char;
707 break;
708 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
709 case BuiltinType::SChar:
710 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_signed_char;
711 break;
712 case BuiltinType::Char8:
713 case BuiltinType::Char16:
714 case BuiltinType::Char32:
715 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_UTF;
716 break;
717 case BuiltinType::UShort:
718 case BuiltinType::UInt:
719 case BuiltinType::UInt128:
720 case BuiltinType::UIntCap:
721 case BuiltinType::ULong:
722 case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
723 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
724 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_unsigned;
725 break;
726 case BuiltinType::Short:
727 case BuiltinType::Int:
728 case BuiltinType::Int128:
729 case BuiltinType::IntCap:
730 case BuiltinType::Long:
731 case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
732 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
733 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_signed;
734 break;
735 case BuiltinType::Bool:
736 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_boolean;
737 break;
738 case BuiltinType::Half:
739 case BuiltinType::Float:
740 case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
741 case BuiltinType::Float16:
742 case BuiltinType::Float128:
743 case BuiltinType::Double:
744 // FIXME: For targets where long double and __float128 have the same size,
745 // they are currently indistinguishable in the debugger without some
746 // special treatment. However, there is currently no consensus on encoding
747 // and this should be updated once a DWARF encoding exists for distinct
748 // floating point types of the same size.
749 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_float;
750 break;
751 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
752 case BuiltinType::Accum:
753 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
754 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
755 case BuiltinType::Fract:
756 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
757 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
758 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
759 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
760 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
761 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
762 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
763 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_signed_fixed;
764 break;
765 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
766 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
767 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
768 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
769 case BuiltinType::UFract:
770 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
771 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
772 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
773 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
774 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
775 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
776 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
777 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_unsigned_fixed;
778 break;
779 }
780
781 switch (BT->getKind()) {
782 case BuiltinType::Long:
783 BTName = "long int";
784 break;
785 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
786 BTName = "long long int";
787 break;
788 case BuiltinType::ULong:
789 BTName = "long unsigned int";
790 break;
791 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
792 BTName = "long long unsigned int";
793 break;
794 default:
795 BTName = BT->getName(CGM.getLangOpts());
796 break;
797 }
798 // Bit size and offset of the type.
799 uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(BT);
800 return DBuilder.createBasicType(BTName, Size, Encoding);
801}

803llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ComplexType *Ty) {
804 // Bit size and offset of the type.
805 llvm::dwarf::TypeKind Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_complex_float;
806 if (Ty->isComplexIntegerType())
807 Encoding = llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_lo_user;
808
809 uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);

812
813llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateQualifiedType(QualType Ty,
814 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
815 QualifierCollector Qc;
816 const Type *T = Qc.strip(Ty);
817
818 // Ignore these qualifiers for now.
819 Qc.removeObjCGCAttr();
820 Qc.removeAddressSpace();
821 Qc.removeObjCLifetime();
822
823 // We will create one Derived type for one qualifier and recurse to handle any
824 // additional ones.
825 llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag;
826 if (Qc.hasConst()) {
827 Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_const_type;
828 Qc.removeConst();
829 } else if (Qc.hasVolatile()) {
830 Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_volatile_type;
831 Qc.removeVolatile();
832 } else if (Qc.hasRestrict()) {
833 Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_restrict_type;
834 Qc.removeRestrict();
835 } else {
836 assert(Qc.empty() && "Unknown type qualifier for debug info");
837 return getOrCreateType(QualType(T, 0), Unit);
838 }
839
840 auto *FromTy = getOrCreateType(Qc.apply(CGM.getContext(), T), Unit);
841
842 // No need to fill in the Name, Line, Size, Alignment, Offset in case of
843 // CVR derived types.
844 return DBuilder.createQualifiedType(Tag, FromTy);
845}

847llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ObjCObjectPointerType *Ty,
848 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
849
850 // The frontend treats 'id' as a typedef to an ObjCObjectType,
851 // whereas 'id<protocol>' is treated as an ObjCPointerType. For the
852 // debug info, we want to emit 'id' in both cases.
853 if (Ty->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
854 return getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getObjCIdType(), Unit);
855
856 return CreatePointerLikeType(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_pointer_type, Ty,
857 Ty->getPointeeType(), Unit);
858}

866/// \return whether a C++ mangling exists for the type defined by TD.
867static bool hasCXXMangling(const TagDecl *TD, llvm::DICompileUnit *TheCU) {
868 switch (TheCU->getSourceLanguage()) {
869 case llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_C_plus_plus:
870 return true;
871 case llvm::dwarf::DW_LANG_ObjC_plus_plus:
872 return isa<CXXRecordDecl>(TD) || isa<EnumDecl>(TD);
873 default:
874 return false;
875 }
876}
877
878// Determines if the debug info for this tag declaration needs a type
879// identifier. The purpose of the unique identifier is to deduplicate type
880// information for identical types across TUs. Because of the C++ one definition
881// rule (ODR), it is valid to assume that the type is defined the same way in
882// every TU and its debug info is equivalent.
883//
884// C does not have the ODR, and it is common for codebases to contain multiple
885// different definitions of a struct with the same name in different TUs.
886// Therefore, if the type doesn't have a C++ mangling, don't give it an
887// identifer. Type information in C is smaller and simpler than C++ type
888// information, so the increase in debug info size is negligible.
889//
890// If the type is not externally visible, it should be unique to the current TU,
891// and should not need an identifier to participate in type deduplication.
892// However, when emitting CodeView, the format internally uses these
893// unique type name identifers for references between debug info. For example,
894// the method of a class in an anonymous namespace uses the identifer to refer
895// to its parent class. The Microsoft C++ ABI attempts to provide unique names
896// for such types, so when emitting CodeView, always use identifiers for C++
897// types. This may create problems when attempting to emit CodeView when the MS
898// C++ ABI is not in use.
899static bool needsTypeIdentifier(const TagDecl *TD, CodeGenModule &CGM,
900 llvm::DICompileUnit *TheCU) {
901 // We only add a type identifier for types with C++ name mangling.
902 if (!hasCXXMangling(TD, TheCU))
903 return false;
904
905 // Externally visible types with C++ mangling need a type identifier.
906 if (TD->isExternallyVisible())
907 return true;
908
909 // CodeView types with C++ mangling need a type identifier.
910 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)
911 return true;
912
913 return false;
914}
915
916// Returns a unique type identifier string if one exists, or an empty string.
917static SmallString<256> getTypeIdentifier(const TagType *Ty, CodeGenModule &CGM,
918 llvm::DICompileUnit *TheCU) {
919 SmallString<256> Identifier;
920 const TagDecl *TD = Ty->getDecl();
921
922 if (!needsTypeIdentifier(TD, CGM, TheCU))
923 return Identifier;
924 if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(TD))
925 if (RD->getDefinition())
926 if (RD->isDynamicClass() &&
927 CGM.getVTableLinkage(RD) == llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage)
928 return Identifier;
929
930 // TODO: This is using the RTTI name. Is there a better way to get
931 // a unique string for a type?
932 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Identifier);
933 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCXXRTTIName(QualType(Ty, 0), Out);
934 return Identifier;
935}
936
937/// \return the appropriate DWARF tag for a composite type.
938static llvm::dwarf::Tag getTagForRecord(const RecordDecl *RD) {
939 llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag;
940 if (RD->isStruct() || RD->isInterface())
941 Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type;
942 else if (RD->isUnion())
943 Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type;
944 else {
945 // FIXME: This could be a struct type giving a default visibility different
946 // than C++ class type, but needs llvm metadata changes first.
947 assert(RD->isClass());
948 Tag = llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type;
949 }
950 return Tag;
951}
952
953llvm::DICompositeType *
954CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateRecordFwdDecl(const RecordType *Ty,
955 llvm::DIScope *Ctx) {
956 const RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
957 if (llvm::DIType *T = getTypeOrNull(CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD)))
958 return cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(T);
959 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation());
960 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(RD->getLocation());
961 StringRef RDName = getClassName(RD);
962
963 uint64_t Size = 0;
964 uint32_t Align = 0;
965
966 // Create the type.
967 SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
968 llvm::DICompositeType *RetTy = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
969 getTagForRecord(RD), RDName, Ctx, DefUnit, Line, 0, Size, Align,
970 llvm::DINode::FlagFwdDecl, Identifier);
971 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugFwdTemplateParams)
972 if (auto *TSpecial = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
973 DBuilder.replaceArrays(RetTy, llvm::DINodeArray(),
974 CollectCXXTemplateParams(TSpecial, DefUnit));
975 ReplaceMap.emplace_back(
976 std::piecewise_construct, std::make_tuple(Ty),
977 std::make_tuple(static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(RetTy)));
978 return RetTy;
979}
980
981llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreatePointerLikeType(llvm::dwarf::Tag Tag,
982 const Type *Ty,
983 QualType PointeeTy,
984 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
985 // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
986 // Size is always the size of a pointer. We can't use getTypeSize here
987 // because that does not return the correct value for references.
988 unsigned AddressSpace;
989 if (Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(CGM.getContext()))
990 AddressSpace = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCHERICapabilityAS();
991 else
992 AddressSpace = CGM.getAddressSpaceForType(PointeeTy);
993 uint64_t Size = CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(AddressSpace);
994 auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
995 Optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
996 CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(AddressSpace);
997
998 if (Tag == llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_reference_type ||
999 Tag == llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_rvalue_reference_type)
1000 return DBuilder.createReferenceType(Tag, getOrCreateType(PointeeTy, Unit),
1001 Size, Align, DWARFAddressSpace);
1002 else
1003 return DBuilder.createPointerType(getOrCreateType(PointeeTy, Unit), Size,
1004 Align, DWARFAddressSpace);
1005}
1006
1007llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateStructPtrType(StringRef Name,
1008 llvm::DIType *&Cache) {
1009 if (Cache)
1010 return Cache;
1011 Cache = DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type, Name,
1012 TheCU, TheCU->getFile(), 0);
1013 unsigned Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1014 Cache = DBuilder.createPointerType(Cache, Size);
1015 return Cache;
1016}
1017
1018uint64_t CGDebugInfo::collectDefaultElementTypesForBlockPointer(
1019 const BlockPointerType *Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit, llvm::DIDerivedType *DescTy,
1020 unsigned LineNo, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys) {
1021 QualType FType;
1022
1023 // Advanced by calls to CreateMemberType in increments of FType, then
1024 // returned as the overall size of the default elements.
1025 uint64_t FieldOffset = 0;
1026
1027 // Blocks in OpenCL have unique constraints which make the standard fields
1028 // redundant while requiring size and align fields for enqueue_kernel. See
1029 // initializeForBlockHeader in CGBlocks.cpp
1030 if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1031 FType = CGM.getContext().IntTy;
1032 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__size", &FieldOffset));
1033 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__align", &FieldOffset));
1034 } else {
1035 FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
1036 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__isa", &FieldOffset));
1037 FType = CGM.getContext().IntTy;
1038 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__flags", &FieldOffset));
1039 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__reserved", &FieldOffset));
1040 FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(Ty->getPointeeType());
1041 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__FuncPtr", &FieldOffset));
1042 FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
1043 uint64_t FieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1044 uint32_t FieldAlign = CGM.getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
1045 EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createMemberType(
1046 Unit, "__descriptor", nullptr, LineNo, FieldSize, FieldAlign,
1047 FieldOffset, llvm::DINode::FlagZero, DescTy));
1048 FieldOffset += FieldSize;
1049 }
1050
1051 return FieldOffset;
1052}
1053
1054llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const BlockPointerType *Ty,
1055 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1056 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> EltTys;
1057 QualType FType;
1058 uint64_t FieldOffset;
1059 llvm::DINodeArray Elements;
1060
1061 FieldOffset = 0;
1062 FType = CGM.getContext().UnsignedLongTy;
1063 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "reserved", &FieldOffset));
1064 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "Size", &FieldOffset));
1065
1066 Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
1067 EltTys.clear();
1068
1069 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagAppleBlock;
1070
1071 auto *EltTy =
1072 DBuilder.createStructType(Unit, "__block_descriptor", nullptr, 0,
1073 FieldOffset, 0, Flags, nullptr, Elements);
1074
1075 // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
1076 uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
1077
1078 auto *DescTy = DBuilder.createPointerType(EltTy, Size);
1079
1080 FieldOffset = collectDefaultElementTypesForBlockPointer(Ty, Unit, DescTy,
1081 0, EltTys);
1082
1083 Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
1084
1085 // The __block_literal_generic structs are marked with a special
1086 // DW_AT_APPLE_BLOCK attribute and are an implementation detail only
1087 // the debugger needs to know about. To allow type uniquing, emit
1088 // them without a name or a location.
1089 EltTy = DBuilder.createStructType(Unit, "", nullptr, 0, FieldOffset, 0,
1090 Flags, nullptr, Elements);
1091
1092 return DBuilder.createPointerType(EltTy, Size);
1093}
1094
1095llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const TemplateSpecializationType *Ty,
1096 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1097 assert(Ty->isTypeAlias());
1098 llvm::DIType *Src = getOrCreateType(Ty->getAliasedType(), Unit);
1099
1100 auto *AliasDecl =
1101 cast<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(Ty->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl())
1102 ->getTemplatedDecl();
1103
1104 if (AliasDecl->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
1105 return Src;
1106
1107 SmallString<128> NS;
1108 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(NS);
1109 Ty->getTemplateName().print(OS, getPrintingPolicy(), /*qualified*/ false);
1110 printTemplateArgumentList(OS, Ty->template_arguments(), getPrintingPolicy());
1111
1112 SourceLocation Loc = AliasDecl->getLocation();
1113 return DBuilder.createTypedef(Src, OS.str(), getOrCreateFile(Loc),
1114 getLineNumber(Loc),
1115 getDeclContextDescriptor(AliasDecl));
1116}
1117
1118llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const TypedefType *Ty,
1119 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1120 llvm::DIType *Underlying =
1121 getOrCreateType(Ty->getDecl()->getUnderlyingType(), Unit);
1122
1123 if (Ty->getDecl()->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
1124 return Underlying;
1125
1126 // We don't set size information, but do specify where the typedef was
1127 // declared.
1128 SourceLocation Loc = Ty->getDecl()->getLocation();
1129
1130 // Typedefs are derived from some other type.
1131 return DBuilder.createTypedef(Underlying, Ty->getDecl()->getName(),
1132 getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc),
1133 getDeclContextDescriptor(Ty->getDecl()));
1134}
1135
1136static unsigned getDwarfCC(CallingConv CC) {
1137 switch (CC) {
1138 case CC_C:
1139 // Avoid emitting DW_AT_calling_convention if the C convention was used.
1140 return 0;
1141
1142 case CC_X86StdCall:
1143 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_stdcall;
1144 case CC_X86FastCall:
1145 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_msfastcall;
1146 case CC_X86ThisCall:
1147 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_thiscall;
1148 case CC_X86VectorCall:
1149 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_vectorcall;
1150 case CC_X86Pascal:
1151 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_BORLAND_pascal;
1152 case CC_Win64:
1153 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_Win64;
1154 case CC_X86_64SysV:
1155 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_X86_64SysV;
1156 case CC_AAPCS:
1157 case CC_AArch64VectorCall:
1158 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_AAPCS;
1159 case CC_AAPCS_VFP:
1160 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_AAPCS_VFP;
1161 case CC_IntelOclBicc:
1162 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_IntelOclBicc;
1163 case CC_SpirFunction:
1164 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_SpirFunction;
1165 case CC_OpenCLKernel:
1166 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_OpenCLKernel;
1167 case CC_Swift:
1168 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_Swift;
1169 case CC_PreserveMost:
1170 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_PreserveMost;
1171 case CC_PreserveAll:
1172 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_PreserveAll;
1173 case CC_CHERICCall:
1174 case CC_CHERICCallee:
1175 case CC_CHERICCallback:
1176 return 0;
1177 case CC_X86RegCall:
1178 return llvm::dwarf::DW_CC_LLVM_X86RegCall;
1179 }
1180 return 0;
1181}
1182
1183llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const FunctionType *Ty,
1184 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1185 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
1186
1187 // Add the result type at least.
1188 EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(Ty->getReturnType(), Unit));
1189
1190 // Set up remainder of arguments if there is a prototype.
1191 // otherwise emit it as a variadic function.
1192 if (isa<FunctionNoProtoType>(Ty))
1193 EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
1194 else if (const auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(Ty)) {
1195 for (const QualType &ParamType : FPT->param_types())
1196 EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(ParamType, Unit));
1197 if (FPT->isVariadic())
1198 EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
1199 }
1200
1201 llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(EltTys);
1202 return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, llvm::DINode::FlagZero,
1203 getDwarfCC(Ty->getCallConv()));
1204}
1205
1206/// Convert an AccessSpecifier into the corresponding DINode flag.
1207/// As an optimization, return 0 if the access specifier equals the
1208/// default for the containing type.
1209static llvm::DINode::DIFlags getAccessFlag(AccessSpecifier Access,
1210 const RecordDecl *RD) {
1211 AccessSpecifier Default = clang::AS_none;
1212 if (RD && RD->isClass())
1213 Default = clang::AS_private;
1214 else if (RD && (RD->isStruct() || RD->isUnion()))
1215 Default = clang::AS_public;
1216
1217 if (Access == Default)
1218 return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1219
1220 switch (Access) {
1221 case clang::AS_private:
1222 return llvm::DINode::FlagPrivate;
1223 case clang::AS_protected:
1224 return llvm::DINode::FlagProtected;
1225 case clang::AS_public:
1226 return llvm::DINode::FlagPublic;
1227 case clang::AS_none:
1228 return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1229 }
1230 llvm_unreachable("unexpected access enumerator");
1231}
1232
1233llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::createBitFieldType(const FieldDecl *BitFieldDecl,
1234 llvm::DIScope *RecordTy,
1235 const RecordDecl *RD) {
1236 StringRef Name = BitFieldDecl->getName();
1237 QualType Ty = BitFieldDecl->getType();
1238 SourceLocation Loc = BitFieldDecl->getLocation();
1239 llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1240 llvm::DIType *DebugType = getOrCreateType(Ty, VUnit);
1241
1242 // Get the location for the field.
1243 llvm::DIFile *File = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1244 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(Loc);
1245
1246 const CGBitFieldInfo &BitFieldInfo =
1247 CGM.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(RD).getBitFieldInfo(BitFieldDecl);
1248 uint64_t SizeInBits = BitFieldInfo.Size;
1249 assert(SizeInBits > 0 && "found named 0-width bitfield");
1250 uint64_t StorageOffsetInBits =
1251 CGM.getContext().toBits(BitFieldInfo.StorageOffset);
1252 uint64_t Offset = BitFieldInfo.Offset;
1253 // The bit offsets for big endian machines are reversed for big
1254 // endian target, compensate for that as the DIDerivedType requires
1255 // un-reversed offsets.
1256 if (CGM.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
1257 Offset = BitFieldInfo.StorageSize - BitFieldInfo.Size - Offset;
1258 uint64_t OffsetInBits = StorageOffsetInBits + Offset;
1259 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = getAccessFlag(BitFieldDecl->getAccess(), RD);
1260 return DBuilder.createBitFieldMemberType(
1261 RecordTy, Name, File, Line, SizeInBits, OffsetInBits, StorageOffsetInBits,
1262 Flags, DebugType);
1263}
1264
1265llvm::DIType *
1266CGDebugInfo::createFieldType(StringRef name, QualType type, SourceLocation loc,
1267 AccessSpecifier AS, uint64_t offsetInBits,
1268 uint32_t AlignInBits, llvm::DIFile *tunit,
1269 llvm::DIScope *scope, const RecordDecl *RD) {
1270 llvm::DIType *debugType = getOrCreateType(type, tunit);
1271
1272 // Get the location for the field.
1273 llvm::DIFile *file = getOrCreateFile(loc);
1274 unsigned line = getLineNumber(loc);
1275
1276 uint64_t SizeInBits = 0;
1277 auto Align = AlignInBits;
1278 if (!type->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
1279 TypeInfo TI = CGM.getContext().getTypeInfo(type);
1280 SizeInBits = TI.Width;
1281 if (!Align)
1282 Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(type, CGM.getContext());
1283 }
1284
1285 llvm::DINode::DIFlags flags = getAccessFlag(AS, RD);
1286 return DBuilder.createMemberType(scope, name, file, line, SizeInBits, Align,
1287 offsetInBits, flags, debugType);
1288}
1289
1290void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordLambdaFields(
1291 const CXXRecordDecl *CXXDecl, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements,
1292 llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
1293 // For C++11 Lambdas a Field will be the same as a Capture, but the Capture
1294 // has the name and the location of the variable so we should iterate over
1295 // both concurrently.
1296 const ASTRecordLayout &layout = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(CXXDecl);
1297 RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = CXXDecl->field_begin();
1298 unsigned fieldno = 0;
1299 for (CXXRecordDecl::capture_const_iterator I = CXXDecl->captures_begin(),
1300 E = CXXDecl->captures_end();
1301 I != E; ++I, ++Field, ++fieldno) {
1302 const LambdaCapture &C = *I;
1303 if (C.capturesVariable()) {
1304 SourceLocation Loc = C.getLocation();
1305 assert(!Field->isBitField() && "lambdas don't have bitfield members!");
1306 VarDecl *V = C.getCapturedVar();
1307 StringRef VName = V->getName();
1308 llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
1309 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(V, CGM.getContext());
1310 llvm::DIType *FieldType = createFieldType(
1311 VName, Field->getType(), Loc, Field->getAccess(),
1312 layout.getFieldOffset(fieldno), Align, VUnit, RecordTy, CXXDecl);
1313 elements.push_back(FieldType);
1314 } else if (C.capturesThis()) {
1315 // TODO: Need to handle 'this' in some way by probably renaming the
1316 // this of the lambda class and having a field member of 'this' or
1317 // by using AT_object_pointer for the function and having that be
1318 // used as 'this' for semantic references.
1319 FieldDecl *f = *Field;
1320 llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(f->getLocation());
1321 QualType type = f->getType();
1322 llvm::DIType *fieldType = createFieldType(
1323 "this", type, f->getLocation(), f->getAccess(),
1324 layout.getFieldOffset(fieldno), VUnit, RecordTy, CXXDecl);
1325
1326 elements.push_back(fieldType);
1327 }
1328 }
1329}
1330
1331llvm::DIDerivedType *
1332CGDebugInfo::CreateRecordStaticField(const VarDecl *Var, llvm::DIType *RecordTy,
1333 const RecordDecl *RD) {
1334 // Create the descriptor for the static variable, with or without
1335 // constant initializers.
1336 Var = Var->getCanonicalDecl();
1337 llvm::DIFile *VUnit = getOrCreateFile(Var->getLocation());
1338 llvm::DIType *VTy = getOrCreateType(Var->getType(), VUnit);
1339
1340 unsigned LineNumber = getLineNumber(Var->getLocation());
1341 StringRef VName = Var->getName();
1342 llvm::Constant *C = nullptr;
1343 if (Var->getInit()) {
1344 const APValue *Value = Var->evaluateValue();
1345 if (Value) {
1346 if (Value->isInt())
1347 C = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Value->getInt());
1348 if (Value->isFloat())
1349 C = llvm::ConstantFP::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Value->getFloat());
1350 }
1351 }
1352
1353 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = getAccessFlag(Var->getAccess(), RD);
1354 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(Var, CGM.getContext());
1355 llvm::DIDerivedType *GV = DBuilder.createStaticMemberType(
1356 RecordTy, VName, VUnit, LineNumber, VTy, Flags, C, Align);
1357 StaticDataMemberCache[Var->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(GV);
1358 return GV;
1359}
1360
1361void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordNormalField(
1362 const FieldDecl *field, uint64_t OffsetInBits, llvm::DIFile *tunit,
1363 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements, llvm::DIType *RecordTy,
1364 const RecordDecl *RD) {
1365 StringRef name = field->getName();
1366 QualType type = field->getType();
1367
1368 // Ignore unnamed fields unless they're anonymous structs/unions.
1369 if (name.empty() && !type->isRecordType())
1370 return;
1371
1372 llvm::DIType *FieldType;
1373 if (field->isBitField()) {
1374 FieldType = createBitFieldType(field, RecordTy, RD);
1375 } else {
1376 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(field, CGM.getContext());
1377 FieldType =
1378 createFieldType(name, type, field->getLocation(), field->getAccess(),
1379 OffsetInBits, Align, tunit, RecordTy, RD);
1380 }
1381
1382 elements.push_back(FieldType);
1383}
1384
1385void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordNestedType(
1386 const TypeDecl *TD, SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements) {
1387 QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getTypeDeclType(TD);
1388 // Injected class names are not considered nested records.
1389 if (isa<InjectedClassNameType>(Ty))
1390 return;
1391 SourceLocation Loc = TD->getLocation();
1392 llvm::DIType *nestedType = getOrCreateType(Ty, getOrCreateFile(Loc));
1393 elements.push_back(nestedType);
1394}
1395
1396void CGDebugInfo::CollectRecordFields(
1397 const RecordDecl *record, llvm::DIFile *tunit,
1398 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &elements,
1399 llvm::DICompositeType *RecordTy) {
1400 const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(record);
1401
1402 if (CXXDecl && CXXDecl->isLambda())
1403 CollectRecordLambdaFields(CXXDecl, elements, RecordTy);
1404 else {
1405 const ASTRecordLayout &layout = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(record);
1406
1407 // Field number for non-static fields.
1408 unsigned fieldNo = 0;
1409
1410 // Static and non-static members should appear in the same order as
1411 // the corresponding declarations in the source program.
1412 for (const auto *I : record->decls())
1413 if (const auto *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(I)) {
1414 if (V->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
1415 continue;
1416
1417 // Skip variable template specializations when emitting CodeView. MSVC
1418 // doesn't emit them.
1419 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView &&
1420 isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(V))
1421 continue;
1422
1423 // Reuse the existing static member declaration if one exists
1424 auto MI = StaticDataMemberCache.find(V->getCanonicalDecl());
1425 if (MI != StaticDataMemberCache.end()) {
1426 assert(MI->second &&
1427 "Static data member declaration should still exist");
1428 elements.push_back(MI->second);
1429 } else {
1430 auto Field = CreateRecordStaticField(V, RecordTy, record);
1431 elements.push_back(Field);
1432 }
1433 } else if (const auto *field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(I)) {
1434 CollectRecordNormalField(field, layout.getFieldOffset(fieldNo), tunit,
1435 elements, RecordTy, record);
1436
1437 // Bump field number for next field.
1438 ++fieldNo;
1439 } else if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView) {
1440 // Debug info for nested types is included in the member list only for
1441 // CodeView.
1442 if (const auto *nestedType = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(I))
1443 if (!nestedType->isImplicit() &&
1444 nestedType->getDeclContext() == record)
1445 CollectRecordNestedType(nestedType, elements);
1446 }
1447 }
1448}
1449
1450llvm::DISubroutineType *
1451CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateMethodType(const CXXMethodDecl *Method,
1452 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1453 const FunctionProtoType *Func = Method->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
1454 if (Method->isStatic())
1455 return cast_or_null<llvm::DISubroutineType>(
1456 getOrCreateType(QualType(Func, 0), Unit));
1457 return getOrCreateInstanceMethodType(Method->getThisType(), Func, Unit);
1458}
1459
1460llvm::DISubroutineType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateInstanceMethodType(
1461 QualType ThisPtr, const FunctionProtoType *Func, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1462 // Add "this" pointer.
1463 llvm::DITypeRefArray Args(
1464 cast<llvm::DISubroutineType>(getOrCreateType(QualType(Func, 0), Unit))
1465 ->getTypeArray());
1466 assert(Args.size() && "Invalid number of arguments!");
1467
1468 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> Elts;
1469
1470 // First element is always return type. For 'void' functions it is NULL.
1471 Elts.push_back(Args[0]);
1472
1473 // "this" pointer is always first argument.
1474 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = ThisPtr->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
1475 if (isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
1476 // Create pointer type directly in this case.
1477 const PointerType *ThisPtrTy = cast<PointerType>(ThisPtr);
1478 QualType PointeeTy = ThisPtrTy->getPointeeType();
1479 unsigned AS = CGM.getAddressSpaceForType(PointeeTy);
1480 uint64_t Size = CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(AS);
1481 auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(ThisPtrTy, CGM.getContext());
1482 llvm::DIType *PointeeType = getOrCreateType(PointeeTy, Unit);
1483 llvm::DIType *ThisPtrType =
1484 DBuilder.createPointerType(PointeeType, Size, Align);
1485 TypeCache[ThisPtr.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(ThisPtrType);
1486 // TODO: This and the artificial type below are misleading, the
1487 // types aren't artificial the argument is, but the current
1488 // metadata doesn't represent that.
1489 ThisPtrType = DBuilder.createObjectPointerType(ThisPtrType);
1490 Elts.push_back(ThisPtrType);
1491 } else {
1492 llvm::DIType *ThisPtrType = getOrCreateType(ThisPtr, Unit);
1493 TypeCache[ThisPtr.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(ThisPtrType);
1494 ThisPtrType = DBuilder.createObjectPointerType(ThisPtrType);
1495 Elts.push_back(ThisPtrType);
1496 }
1497
1498 // Copy rest of the arguments.
1499 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Args.size(); i != e; ++i)
1500 Elts.push_back(Args[i]);
1501
1502 llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(Elts);
1503
1504 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1505 if (Func->getExtProtoInfo().RefQualifier == RQ_LValue)
1506 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagLValueReference;
1507 if (Func->getExtProtoInfo().RefQualifier == RQ_RValue)
1508 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagRValueReference;
1509
1510 return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, Flags,
1511 getDwarfCC(Func->getCallConv()));
1512}
1513
1514/// isFunctionLocalClass - Return true if CXXRecordDecl is defined
1515/// inside a function.
1516static bool isFunctionLocalClass(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
1517 if (const auto *NRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD->getDeclContext()))
1518 return isFunctionLocalClass(NRD);
1519 if (isa<FunctionDecl>(RD->getDeclContext()))
1520 return true;
1521 return false;
1522}
1523
1524llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::CreateCXXMemberFunction(
1525 const CXXMethodDecl *Method, llvm::DIFile *Unit, llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
1526 bool IsCtorOrDtor =
1527 isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method);
1528
1529 StringRef MethodName = getFunctionName(Method);
1530 llvm::DISubroutineType *MethodTy = getOrCreateMethodType(Method, Unit);
1531
1532 // Since a single ctor/dtor corresponds to multiple functions, it doesn't
1533 // make sense to give a single ctor/dtor a linkage name.
1534 StringRef MethodLinkageName;
1535 // FIXME: 'isFunctionLocalClass' seems like an arbitrary/unintentional
1536 // property to use here. It may've been intended to model "is non-external
1537 // type" but misses cases of non-function-local but non-external classes such
1538 // as those in anonymous namespaces as well as the reverse - external types
1539 // that are function local, such as those in (non-local) inline functions.
1540 if (!IsCtorOrDtor && !isFunctionLocalClass(Method->getParent()))
1541 MethodLinkageName = CGM.getMangledName(Method);
1542
1543 // Get the location for the method.
1544 llvm::DIFile *MethodDefUnit = nullptr;
1545 unsigned MethodLine = 0;
1546 if (!Method->isImplicit()) {
1547 MethodDefUnit = getOrCreateFile(Method->getLocation());
1548 MethodLine = getLineNumber(Method->getLocation());
1549 }
1550
1551 // Collect virtual method info.
1552 llvm::DIType *ContainingType = nullptr;
1553 unsigned VIndex = 0;
1554 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
1555 llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
1556 int ThisAdjustment = 0;
1557
1558 if (Method->isVirtual()) {
1559 if (Method->isPure())
1560 SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagPureVirtual;
1561 else
1562 SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagVirtual;
1563
1564 if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isItaniumFamily()) {
1565 // It doesn't make sense to give a virtual destructor a vtable index,
1566 // since a single destructor has two entries in the vtable.
1567 if (!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method))
1568 VIndex = CGM.getItaniumVTableContext().getMethodVTableIndex(Method);
1569 } else {
1570 // Emit MS ABI vftable information. There is only one entry for the
1571 // deleting dtor.
1572 const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method);
1573 GlobalDecl GD = DD ? GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Deleting) : GlobalDecl(Method);
1574 MethodVFTableLocation ML =
1575 CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getMethodVFTableLocation(GD);
1576 VIndex = ML.Index;
1577
1578 // CodeView only records the vftable offset in the class that introduces
1579 // the virtual method. This is possible because, unlike Itanium, the MS
1580 // C++ ABI does not include all virtual methods from non-primary bases in
1581 // the vtable for the most derived class. For example, if C inherits from
1582 // A and B, C's primary vftable will not include B's virtual methods.
1583 if (Method->size_overridden_methods() == 0)
1584 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagIntroducedVirtual;
1585
1586 // The 'this' adjustment accounts for both the virtual and non-virtual
1587 // portions of the adjustment. Presumably the debugger only uses it when
1588 // it knows the dynamic type of an object.
1589 ThisAdjustment = CGM.getCXXABI()
1590 .getVirtualFunctionPrologueThisAdjustment(GD)
1591 .getQuantity();
1592 }
1593 ContainingType = RecordTy;
1594 }
1595
1596 if (Method->isStatic())
1597 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagStaticMember;
1598 if (Method->isImplicit())
1599 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
1600 Flags |= getAccessFlag(Method->getAccess(), Method->getParent());
1601 if (const auto *CXXC = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method)) {
1602 if (CXXC->isExplicit())
1603 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagExplicit;
1604 } else if (const auto *CXXC = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(Method)) {
1605 if (CXXC->isExplicit())
1606 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagExplicit;
1607 }
1608 if (Method->hasPrototype())
1609 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
1610 if (Method->getRefQualifier() == RQ_LValue)
1611 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagLValueReference;
1612 if (Method->getRefQualifier() == RQ_RValue)
1613 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagRValueReference;
1614 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
1615 SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
1616
1617 llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray = CollectFunctionTemplateParams(Method, Unit);
1618 llvm::DISubprogram *SP = DBuilder.createMethod(
1619 RecordTy, MethodName, MethodLinkageName, MethodDefUnit, MethodLine,
1620 MethodTy, VIndex, ThisAdjustment, ContainingType, Flags, SPFlags,
1621 TParamsArray.get());
1622
1623 SPCache[Method->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(SP);
1624
1625 return SP;
1626}
1627
1628void CGDebugInfo::CollectCXXMemberFunctions(
1629 const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
1630 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys, llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
1631
1632 // Since we want more than just the individual member decls if we
1633 // have templated functions iterate over every declaration to gather
1634 // the functions.
1635 for (const auto *I : RD->decls()) {
1636 const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(I);
1637 // If the member is implicit, don't add it to the member list. This avoids
1638 // the member being added to type units by LLVM, while still allowing it
1639 // to be emitted into the type declaration/reference inside the compile
1640 // unit.
1641 // Ditto 'nodebug' methods, for consistency with CodeGenFunction.cpp.
1642 // FIXME: Handle Using(Shadow?)Decls here to create
1643 // DW_TAG_imported_declarations inside the class for base decls brought into
1644 // derived classes. GDB doesn't seem to notice/leverage these when I tried
1645 // it, so I'm not rushing to fix this. (GCC seems to produce them, if
1646 // referenced)
1647 if (!Method || Method->isImplicit() || Method->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
1648 continue;
1649
1650 if (Method->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getContainedAutoType())
1651 continue;
1652
1653 // Reuse the existing member function declaration if it exists.
1654 // It may be associated with the declaration of the type & should be
1655 // reused as we're building the definition.
1656 //
1657 // This situation can arise in the vtable-based debug info reduction where
1658 // implicit members are emitted in a non-vtable TU.
1659 auto MI = SPCache.find(Method->getCanonicalDecl());
1660 EltTys.push_back(MI == SPCache.end()
1661 ? CreateCXXMemberFunction(Method, Unit, RecordTy)
1662 : static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(MI->second));
1663 }
1664}
1665
1666void CGDebugInfo::CollectCXXBases(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
1667 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys,
1668 llvm::DIType *RecordTy) {
1669 llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const CXXRecordDecl>> SeenTypes;
1670 CollectCXXBasesAux(RD, Unit, EltTys, RecordTy, RD->bases(), SeenTypes,
1671 llvm::DINode::FlagZero);
1672
1673 // If we are generating CodeView debug info, we also need to emit records for
1674 // indirect virtual base classes.
1675 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView) {
1676 CollectCXXBasesAux(RD, Unit, EltTys, RecordTy, RD->vbases(), SeenTypes,
1677 llvm::DINode::FlagIndirectVirtualBase);
1678 }
1679}
1680
1681void CGDebugInfo::CollectCXXBasesAux(
1682 const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
1683 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys, llvm::DIType *RecordTy,
1684 const CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_range &Bases,
1685 llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const CXXRecordDecl>> &SeenTypes,
1686 llvm::DINode::DIFlags StartingFlags) {
1687 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
1688 for (const auto &BI : Bases) {
1689 const auto *Base =
1690 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BI.getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1691 if (!SeenTypes.insert(Base).second)
1692 continue;
1693 auto *BaseTy = getOrCreateType(BI.getType(), Unit);
1694 llvm::DINode::DIFlags BFlags = StartingFlags;
1695 uint64_t BaseOffset;
1696 uint32_t VBPtrOffset = 0;
1697
1698 if (BI.isVirtual()) {
1699 if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isItaniumFamily()) {
1700 // virtual base offset offset is -ve. The code generator emits dwarf
1701 // expression where it expects +ve number.
1702 BaseOffset = 0 - CGM.getItaniumVTableContext()
1703 .getVirtualBaseOffsetOffset(RD, Base)
1704 .getQuantity();
1705 } else {
1706 // In the MS ABI, store the vbtable offset, which is analogous to the
1707 // vbase offset offset in Itanium.
1708 BaseOffset =
1709 4 * CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getVBTableIndex(RD, Base);
1710 VBPtrOffset = CGM.getContext()
1711 .getASTRecordLayout(RD)
1712 .getVBPtrOffset()
1713 .getQuantity();
1714 }
1715 BFlags |= llvm::DINode::FlagVirtual;
1716 } else
1717 BaseOffset = CGM.getContext().toBits(RL.getBaseClassOffset(Base));
1718 // FIXME: Inconsistent units for BaseOffset. It is in bytes when
1719 // BI->isVirtual() and bits when not.
1720
1721 BFlags |= getAccessFlag(BI.getAccessSpecifier(), RD);
1722 llvm::DIType *DTy = DBuilder.createInheritance(RecordTy, BaseTy, BaseOffset,
1723 VBPtrOffset, BFlags);
1724 EltTys.push_back(DTy);
1725 }
1726}
1727
1728llvm::DINodeArray
1729CGDebugInfo::CollectTemplateParams(const TemplateParameterList *TPList,
1730 ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> TAList,
1731 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1732 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> TemplateParams;
1733 for (unsigned i = 0, e = TAList.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1734 const TemplateArgument &TA = TAList[i];
1735 StringRef Name;
1736 if (TPList)
1737 Name = TPList->getParam(i)->getName();
1738 switch (TA.getKind()) {
1739 case TemplateArgument::Type: {
1740 llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(TA.getAsType(), Unit);
1741 TemplateParams.push_back(
1742 DBuilder.createTemplateTypeParameter(TheCU, Name, TTy));
1743 } break;
1744 case TemplateArgument::Integral: {
1745 llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(TA.getIntegralType(), Unit);
1746 TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
1747 TheCU, Name, TTy,
1748 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), TA.getAsIntegral())));
1749 } break;
1750 case TemplateArgument::Declaration: {
1751 const ValueDecl *D = TA.getAsDecl();
1752 QualType T = TA.getParamTypeForDecl().getDesugaredType(CGM.getContext());
1753 llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
1754 llvm::Constant *V = nullptr;
1755 // Skip retrieve the value if that template parameter has cuda device
1756 // attribute, i.e. that value is not available at the host side.
1757 if (!CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA || CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice ||
1758 !D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
1759 const CXXMethodDecl *MD;
1760 // Variable pointer template parameters have a value that is the address
1761 // of the variable.
1762 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
1763 V = CGM.GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
1764 // Member function pointers have special support for building them,
1765 // though this is currently unsupported in LLVM CodeGen.
1766 else if ((MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) && MD->isInstance())
1767 V = CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberFunctionPointerGlobal(MD);
1768 else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
1769 V = CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(FD);
1770 // Member data pointers have special handling too to compute the fixed
1771 // offset within the object.
1772 else if (const auto *MPT =
1773 dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(T.getTypePtr())) {
1774 // These five lines (& possibly the above member function pointer
1775 // handling) might be able to be refactored to use similar code in
1776 // CodeGenModule::getMemberPointerConstant
1777 uint64_t fieldOffset = CGM.getContext().getFieldOffset(D);
1778 CharUnits chars =
1779 CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits((int64_t)fieldOffset);
1780 V = CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberDataPointer(MPT, chars);
1781 }
1782 V = V->stripPointerCasts();
1783 }
1784 TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
1785 TheCU, Name, TTy, cast_or_null<llvm::Constant>(V)));
1786 } break;
1787 case TemplateArgument::NullPtr: {
1788 QualType T = TA.getNullPtrType();
1789 llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
1790 llvm::Constant *V = nullptr;
1791 // Special case member data pointer null values since they're actually -1
1792 // instead of zero.
1793 if (const auto *MPT = dyn_cast<MemberPointerType>(T.getTypePtr()))
1794 // But treat member function pointers as simple zero integers because
1795 // it's easier than having a special case in LLVM's CodeGen. If LLVM
1796 // CodeGen grows handling for values of non-null member function
1797 // pointers then perhaps we could remove this special case and rely on
1798 // EmitNullMemberPointer for member function pointers.
1799 if (MPT->isMemberDataPointer())
1800 V = CGM.getCXXABI().EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
1801 if (!V)
1802 V = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int8Ty, 0);
1803 TemplateParams.push_back(
1804 DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(TheCU, Name, TTy, V));
1805 } break;
1806 case TemplateArgument::Template:
1807 TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateTemplateParameter(
1808 TheCU, Name, nullptr,
1809 TA.getAsTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl()->getQualifiedNameAsString()));
1810 break;
1811 case TemplateArgument::Pack:
1812 TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateParameterPack(
1813 TheCU, Name, nullptr,
1814 CollectTemplateParams(nullptr, TA.getPackAsArray(), Unit)));
1815 break;
1816 case TemplateArgument::Expression: {
1817 const Expr *E = TA.getAsExpr();
1818 QualType T = E->getType();
1819 if (E->isGLValue())
1820 T = CGM.getContext().getLValueReferenceType(T);
1821 llvm::Constant *V = ConstantEmitter(CGM).emitAbstract(E, T);
1822 assert(V && "Expression in template argument isn't constant");
1823 llvm::DIType *TTy = getOrCreateType(T, Unit);
1824 TemplateParams.push_back(DBuilder.createTemplateValueParameter(
1825 TheCU, Name, TTy, V->stripPointerCasts()));
1826 } break;
1827 // And the following should never occur:
1828 case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
1829 case TemplateArgument::Null:
1830 llvm_unreachable(
1831 "These argument types shouldn't exist in concrete types");
1832 }
1833 }
1834 return DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(TemplateParams);
1835}

1852 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {

1876llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateVTablePtrType(llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
1877 if (VTablePtrType)
1878 return VTablePtrType;
1879
1880 ASTContext &Context = CGM.getContext();
1881
1882 /* Function type */
1883 llvm::Metadata *STy = getOrCreateType(Context.IntTy, Unit);
1884 llvm::DITypeRefArray SElements = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(STy);
1885 llvm::DIType *SubTy = DBuilder.createSubroutineType(SElements);
1886 unsigned Size = Context.getTypeSize(Context.VoidPtrTy);
1887 unsigned VtblPtrAddressSpace = CGM.getTarget().getVtblPtrAddressSpace();
1888 Optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
1889 CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(VtblPtrAddressSpace);
1890
1891 llvm::DIType *vtbl_ptr_type = DBuilder.createPointerType(
1892 SubTy, Size, 0, DWARFAddressSpace, "__vtbl_ptr_type");
1893 VTablePtrType = DBuilder.createPointerType(vtbl_ptr_type, Size);
1894 return VTablePtrType;
1895}

1901
1902StringRef CGDebugInfo::getDynamicInitializerName(const VarDecl *VD,
1903 DynamicInitKind StubKind,
1904 llvm::Function *InitFn) {
1905 // If we're not emitting codeview, use the mangled name. For Itanium, this is
1906 // arbitrary.
1907 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)
1908 return InitFn->getName();
1909
1910 // Print the normal qualified name for the variable, then break off the last
1911 // NNS, and add the appropriate other text. Clang always prints the global
1912 // variable name without template arguments, so we can use rsplit("::") and
1913 // then recombine the pieces.
1914 SmallString<128> QualifiedGV;
1915 StringRef Quals;
1916 StringRef GVName;
1917 {
1918 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(QualifiedGV);
1919 VD->printQualifiedName(OS, getPrintingPolicy());
1920 std::tie(Quals, GVName) = OS.str().rsplit("::");
1921 if (GVName.empty())
1922 std::swap(Quals, GVName);
1923 }
1924
1925 SmallString<128> InitName;
1926 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(InitName);
1927 if (!Quals.empty())
1928 OS << Quals << "::";
1929
1930 switch (StubKind) {
1931 case DynamicInitKind::NoStub:
1932 llvm_unreachable("not an initializer");
1933 case DynamicInitKind::Initializer:
1934 OS << "`dynamic initializer for '";
1935 break;
1936 case DynamicInitKind::AtExit:
1937 OS << "`dynamic atexit destructor for '";
1938 break;
1939 }
1940
1941 OS << GVName;
1942
1943 // Add any template specialization args.
1944 if (const auto *VTpl = dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD)) {
1945 printTemplateArgumentList(OS, VTpl->getTemplateArgs().asArray(),
1946 getPrintingPolicy());
1947 }
1948
1949 OS << '\'';
1950
1951 return internString(OS.str());
1952}
1953
1954void CGDebugInfo::CollectVTableInfo(const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
1955 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &EltTys,
1956 llvm::DICompositeType *RecordTy) {
1957 // If this class is not dynamic then there is not any vtable info to collect.
1958 if (!RD->isDynamicClass())
1959 return;
1960
1961 // Don't emit any vtable shape or vptr info if this class doesn't have an
1962 // extendable vfptr. This can happen if the class doesn't have virtual
1963 // methods, or in the MS ABI if those virtual methods only come from virtually
1964 // inherited bases.
1965 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
1966 if (!RL.hasExtendableVFPtr())
1967 return;
1968
1969 // CodeView needs to know how large the vtable of every dynamic class is, so
1970 // emit a special named pointer type into the element list. The vptr type
1971 // points to this type as well.
1972 llvm::DIType *VPtrTy = nullptr;
1973 bool NeedVTableShape = CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView &&
1974 CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft();
1975 if (NeedVTableShape) {
1976 uint64_t PtrWidth =
1977 CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1978 const VTableLayout &VFTLayout =
1979 CGM.getMicrosoftVTableContext().getVFTableLayout(RD, CharUnits::Zero());
1980 unsigned VSlotCount =
1981 VFTLayout.vtable_components().size() - CGM.getLangOpts().RTTIData;
1982 unsigned VTableWidth = PtrWidth * VSlotCount;
1983 unsigned VtblPtrAddressSpace = CGM.getTarget().getVtblPtrAddressSpace();
1984 Optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
1985 CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(VtblPtrAddressSpace);
1986
1987 // Create a very wide void* type and insert it directly in the element list.
1988 llvm::DIType *VTableType = DBuilder.createPointerType(
1989 nullptr, VTableWidth, 0, DWARFAddressSpace, "__vtbl_ptr_type");
1990 EltTys.push_back(VTableType);
1991
1992 // The vptr is a pointer to this special vtable type.
1993 VPtrTy = DBuilder.createPointerType(VTableType, PtrWidth);
1994 }
1995
1996 // If there is a primary base then the artificial vptr member lives there.
1997 if (RL.getPrimaryBase())
1998 return;
1999
2000 if (!VPtrTy)
2001 VPtrTy = getOrCreateVTablePtrType(Unit);
2002
2003 unsigned Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(CGM.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
2004 llvm::DIType *VPtrMember =
2005 DBuilder.createMemberType(Unit, getVTableName(RD), Unit, 0, Size, 0, 0,
2006 llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial, VPtrTy);
2007 EltTys.push_back(VPtrMember);
2008}

2066/// Return true if the class or any of its methods are marked dllimport.
2067static bool isClassOrMethodDLLImport(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2068 if (RD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
2069 return true;
2070 for (const CXXMethodDecl *MD : RD->methods())
2071 if (MD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
2072 return true;
2073 return false;
2074}
2075
2076/// Does a type definition exist in an imported clang module?
2077static bool isDefinedInClangModule(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2078 // Only definitions that where imported from an AST file come from a module.
2079 if (!RD || !RD->isFromASTFile())
2080 return false;
2081 // Anonymous entities cannot be addressed. Treat them as not from module.
2082 if (!RD->isExternallyVisible() && RD->getName().empty())
2083 return false;
2084 if (auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
2085 if (!CXXDecl->isCompleteDefinition())
2086 return false;
2087 // Check wether RD is a template.
2088 auto TemplateKind = CXXDecl->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
2089 if (TemplateKind != TSK_Undeclared) {
2090 // Unfortunately getOwningModule() isn't accurate enough to find the
2091 // owning module of a ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl that is inside a
2092 // namespace spanning multiple modules.
2093 bool Explicit = false;
2094 if (auto *TD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(CXXDecl))
2095 Explicit = TD->isExplicitInstantiationOrSpecialization();
2096 if (!Explicit && CXXDecl->getEnclosingNamespaceContext())
2097 return false;
2098 // This is a template, check the origin of the first member.
2099 if (CXXDecl->field_begin() == CXXDecl->field_end())
2100 return TemplateKind == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration;
2101 if (!CXXDecl->field_begin()->isFromASTFile())
2102 return false;
2103 }
2104 }
2105 return true;
2106}

2108void CGDebugInfo::completeClassData(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2109 if (auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
2110 if (CXXRD->isDynamicClass() &&
2111 CGM.getVTableLinkage(CXXRD) ==
2112 llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage &&
2113 !isClassOrMethodDLLImport(CXXRD))
2114 return;
2115
2116 if (DebugTypeExtRefs && isDefinedInClangModule(RD->getDefinition()))
2117 return;
2118
2119 completeClass(RD);
2120}

2122void CGDebugInfo::completeClass(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2123 if (DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
2124 return;
2125 QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD);
2126 void *TyPtr = Ty.getAsOpaquePtr();
2127 auto I = TypeCache.find(TyPtr);
2128 if (I != TypeCache.end() && !cast<llvm::DIType>(I->second)->isForwardDecl())
2129 return;
2130 llvm::DIType *Res = CreateTypeDefinition(Ty->castAs<RecordType>());
2131 assert(!Res->isForwardDecl());
2132 TypeCache[TyPtr].reset(Res);
2133}

2135static bool hasExplicitMemberDefinition(CXXRecordDecl::method_iterator I,
2136 CXXRecordDecl::method_iterator End) {
2137 for (CXXMethodDecl *MD : llvm::make_range(I, End))
2138 if (FunctionDecl *Tmpl = MD->getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction())
2139 if (!Tmpl->isImplicit() && Tmpl->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
2140 !MD->getMemberSpecializationInfo()->isExplicitSpecialization())
2141 return true;
2142 return false;
2143}
2144
2145static bool shouldOmitDefinition(codegenoptions::DebugInfoKind DebugKind,
2146 bool DebugTypeExtRefs, const RecordDecl *RD,
2147 const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
2148 if (DebugTypeExtRefs && isDefinedInClangModule(RD->getDefinition()))
2149 return true;
2150
2151 if (auto *ES = RD->getASTContext().getExternalSource())
2152 if (ES->hasExternalDefinitions(RD) == ExternalASTSource::EK_Always)
2153 return true;
2154
2155 if (DebugKind > codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo)
2156 return false;
2157
2158 if (!LangOpts.CPlusPlus)
2159 return false;
2160
2161 if (!RD->isCompleteDefinitionRequired())
2162 return true;
2163
2164 const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
2165
2166 if (!CXXDecl)
2167 return false;
2168
2169 // Only emit complete debug info for a dynamic class when its vtable is
2170 // emitted. However, Microsoft debuggers don't resolve type information
2171 // across DLL boundaries, so skip this optimization if the class or any of its
2172 // methods are marked dllimport. This isn't a complete solution, since objects
2173 // without any dllimport methods can be used in one DLL and constructed in
2174 // another, but it is the current behavior of LimitedDebugInfo.
2175 if (CXXDecl->hasDefinition() && CXXDecl->isDynamicClass() &&
2176 !isClassOrMethodDLLImport(CXXDecl))
2177 return true;
2178
2179 TemplateSpecializationKind Spec = TSK_Undeclared;
2180 if (const auto *SD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
2181 Spec = SD->getSpecializationKind();
2182
2183 if (Spec == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration &&
2184 hasExplicitMemberDefinition(CXXDecl->method_begin(),
2185 CXXDecl->method_end()))
2186 return true;
2187
2188 return false;
2189}
2190
2191void CGDebugInfo::completeRequiredType(const RecordDecl *RD) {
2192 if (shouldOmitDefinition(DebugKind, DebugTypeExtRefs, RD, CGM.getLangOpts()))
2193 return;
2194
2195 QualType Ty = CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD);
2196 llvm::DIType *T = getTypeOrNull(Ty);
2197 if (T && T->isForwardDecl())
2198 completeClassData(RD);
2199}
