2213
2214llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeDefinition(const RecordType *Ty) {
2215 RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
2216
2217 // Get overall information about the record type for the debug info.
2218 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation());
2219
2220 // Records and classes and unions can all be recursive. To handle them, we
2221 // first generate a debug descriptor for the struct as a forward declaration.
2222 // Then (if it is a definition) we go through and get debug info for all of
2223 // its members. Finally, we create a descriptor for the complete type (which
2224 // may refer to the forward decl if the struct is recursive) and replace all
2225 // uses of the forward declaration with the final definition.
2226 llvm::DICompositeType *FwdDecl = getOrCreateLimitedType(Ty, DefUnit);
2227
2228 const RecordDecl *D = RD->getDefinition();
2229 if (!D || !D->isCompleteDefinition())
2230 return FwdDecl;
2231
2232 if (const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
2233 CollectContainingType(CXXDecl, FwdDecl);
2234
2235 // Push the struct on region stack.
2236 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(&*FwdDecl);
2237 RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(FwdDecl);
2238
2239 // Convert all the elements.
2240 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
2241 // what about nested types?
2242
2243 // Note: The split of CXXDecl information here is intentional, the
2244 // gdb tests will depend on a certain ordering at printout. The debug
2245 // information offsets are still correct if we merge them all together
2246 // though.
2247 const auto *CXXDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD);
2248 if (CXXDecl) {
2249 CollectCXXBases(CXXDecl, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2250 CollectVTableInfo(CXXDecl, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2251 }
2252
2253 // Collect data fields (including static variables and any initializers).
2254 CollectRecordFields(RD, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2255 if (CXXDecl)
2256 CollectCXXMemberFunctions(CXXDecl, DefUnit, EltTys, FwdDecl);
2257
2258 LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
2259 RegionMap.erase(Ty->getDecl());
2260
2261 llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
2262 DBuilder.replaceArrays(FwdDecl, Elements);
2263
2264 if (FwdDecl->isTemporary())
2265 FwdDecl =
2266 llvm::MDNode::replaceWithPermanent(llvm::TempDICompositeType(FwdDecl));
2267
2268 RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(FwdDecl);
2269 return FwdDecl;
2270}

2313
2314llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ObjCInterfaceType *Ty,
2315 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2316 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = Ty->getDecl();
2317 if (!ID)
2318 return nullptr;
2319
2320 // Return a forward declaration if this type was imported from a clang module,
2321 // and this is not the compile unit with the implementation of the type (which
2322 // may contain hidden ivars).
2323 if (DebugTypeExtRefs && ID->isFromASTFile() && ID->getDefinition() &&
2324 !ID->getImplementation())
2325 return DBuilder.createForwardDecl(llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type,
2326 ID->getName(),
2327 getDeclContextDescriptor(ID), Unit, 0);
2328
2329 // Get overall information about the record type for the debug info.
2330 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ID->getLocation());
2331 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ID->getLocation());
2332 auto RuntimeLang =
2333 static_cast<llvm::dwarf::SourceLanguage>(TheCU->getSourceLanguage());
2334
2335 // If this is just a forward declaration return a special forward-declaration
2336 // debug type since we won't be able to lay out the entire type.
2337 ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = ID->getDefinition();
2338 if (!Def || !Def->getImplementation()) {
2339 llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(ID);
2340 llvm::DIType *FwdDecl = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
2341 llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type, ID->getName(), Mod ? Mod : TheCU,
2342 DefUnit, Line, RuntimeLang);
2343 ObjCInterfaceCache.push_back(ObjCInterfaceCacheEntry(Ty, FwdDecl, Unit));
2344 return FwdDecl;
2345 }
2346
2347 return CreateTypeDefinition(Ty, Unit);
2348}
2349
2350llvm::DIModule *
2351CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateModuleRef(ExternalASTSource::ASTSourceDescriptor Mod,
2352 bool CreateSkeletonCU) {
2353 // Use the Module pointer as the key into the cache. This is a
2354 // nullptr if the "Module" is a PCH, which is safe because we don't
2355 // support chained PCH debug info, so there can only be a single PCH.
2356 const Module *M = Mod.getModuleOrNull();
2357 auto ModRef = ModuleCache.find(M);
2358 if (ModRef != ModuleCache.end())
2359 return cast<llvm::DIModule>(ModRef->second);
2360
2361 // Macro definitions that were defined with "-D" on the command line.
2362 SmallString<128> ConfigMacros;
2363 {
2364 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(ConfigMacros);
2365 const auto &PPOpts = CGM.getPreprocessorOpts();
2366 unsigned I = 0;
2367 // Translate the macro definitions back into a command line.
2368 for (auto &M : PPOpts.Macros) {
2369 if (++I > 1)
2370 OS << " ";
2371 const std::string &Macro = M.first;
2372 bool Undef = M.second;
2373 OS << "\"-" << (Undef ? 'U' : 'D');
2374 for (char c : Macro)
2375 switch (c) {
2376 case '\\':
2377 OS << "\\\\";
2378 break;
2379 case '"':
2380 OS << "\\\"";
2381 break;
2382 default:
2383 OS << c;
2384 }
2385 OS << '\"';
2386 }
2387 }
2388
2389 bool IsRootModule = M ? !M->Parent : true;
2390 // When a module name is specified as -fmodule-name, that module gets a
2391 // clang::Module object, but it won't actually be built or imported; it will
2392 // be textual.
2393 if (CreateSkeletonCU && IsRootModule && Mod.getASTFile().empty() && M)
2394 assert(StringRef(M->Name).startswith(CGM.getLangOpts().ModuleName) &&
2395 "clang module without ASTFile must be specified by -fmodule-name");
2396
2397 if (CreateSkeletonCU && IsRootModule && !Mod.getASTFile().empty()) {
2398 // PCH files don't have a signature field in the control block,
2399 // but LLVM detects skeleton CUs by looking for a non-zero DWO id.
2400 // We use the lower 64 bits for debug info.
2401 uint64_t Signature =
2402 Mod.getSignature()
2403 ? (uint64_t)Mod.getSignature()[1] << 32 | Mod.getSignature()[0]
2404 : ~1ULL;
2405 llvm::DIBuilder DIB(CGM.getModule());
2406 DIB.createCompileUnit(TheCU->getSourceLanguage(),
2407 // TODO: Support "Source" from external AST providers?
2408 DIB.createFile(Mod.getModuleName(), Mod.getPath()),
2409 TheCU->getProducer(), true, StringRef(), 0,
2410 Mod.getASTFile(), llvm::DICompileUnit::FullDebug,
2411 Signature);
2412 DIB.finalize();
2413 }
2414
2415 llvm::DIModule *Parent =
2416 IsRootModule ? nullptr
2417 : getOrCreateModuleRef(
2418 ExternalASTSource::ASTSourceDescriptor(*M->Parent),
2419 CreateSkeletonCU);
2420 llvm::DIModule *DIMod =
2421 DBuilder.createModule(Parent, Mod.getModuleName(), ConfigMacros,
2422 Mod.getPath(), CGM.getHeaderSearchOpts().Sysroot);
2423 ModuleCache[M].reset(DIMod);
2424 return DIMod;
2425}
2426
2427llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeDefinition(const ObjCInterfaceType *Ty,
2428 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2429 ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = Ty->getDecl();
2430 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ID->getLocation());
2431 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ID->getLocation());
2432 unsigned RuntimeLang = TheCU->getSourceLanguage();
2433
2434 // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
2435 uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
2436 auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
2437
2438 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
2439 if (ID->getImplementation())
2440 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagObjcClassComplete;
2441
2442 llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(ID);
2443 llvm::DICompositeType *RealDecl = DBuilder.createStructType(
2444 Mod ? Mod : Unit, ID->getName(), DefUnit, Line, Size, Align, Flags,
2445 nullptr, llvm::DINodeArray(), RuntimeLang);
2446
2447 QualType QTy(Ty, 0);
2448 TypeCache[QTy.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(RealDecl);
2449
2450 // Push the struct on region stack.
2451 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(RealDecl);
2452 RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(RealDecl);
2453
2454 // Convert all the elements.
2455 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
2456
2457 ObjCInterfaceDecl *SClass = ID->getSuperClass();
2458 if (SClass) {
2459 llvm::DIType *SClassTy =
2460 getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getObjCInterfaceType(SClass), Unit);
2461 if (!SClassTy)
2462 return nullptr;
2463
2464 llvm::DIType *InhTag = DBuilder.createInheritance(RealDecl, SClassTy, 0, 0,
2465 llvm::DINode::FlagZero);
2466 EltTys.push_back(InhTag);
2467 }
2468
2469 // Create entries for all of the properties.
2470 auto AddProperty = [&](const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD) {
2471 SourceLocation Loc = PD->getLocation();
2472 llvm::DIFile *PUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
2473 unsigned PLine = getLineNumber(Loc);
2474 ObjCMethodDecl *Getter = PD->getGetterMethodDecl();
2475 ObjCMethodDecl *Setter = PD->getSetterMethodDecl();
2476 llvm::MDNode *PropertyNode = DBuilder.createObjCProperty(
2477 PD->getName(), PUnit, PLine,
2478 hasDefaultGetterName(PD, Getter) ? ""
2479 : getSelectorName(PD->getGetterName()),
2480 hasDefaultSetterName(PD, Setter) ? ""
2481 : getSelectorName(PD->getSetterName()),
2482 PD->getPropertyAttributes(), getOrCreateType(PD->getType(), PUnit));
2483 EltTys.push_back(PropertyNode);
2484 };
2485 {
2486 llvm::SmallPtrSet<const IdentifierInfo *, 16> PropertySet;
2487 for (const ObjCCategoryDecl *ClassExt : ID->known_extensions())
2488 for (auto *PD : ClassExt->properties()) {
2489 PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier());
2490 AddProperty(PD);
2491 }
2492 for (const auto *PD : ID->properties()) {
2493 // Don't emit duplicate metadata for properties that were already in a
2494 // class extension.
2495 if (!PropertySet.insert(PD->getIdentifier()).second)
2496 continue;
2497 AddProperty(PD);
2498 }
2499 }
2500
2501 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(ID);
2502 unsigned FieldNo = 0;
2503 for (ObjCIvarDecl *Field = ID->all_declared_ivar_begin(); Field;
2504 Field = Field->getNextIvar(), ++FieldNo) {
2505 llvm::DIType *FieldTy = getOrCreateType(Field->getType(), Unit);
2506 if (!FieldTy)
2507 return nullptr;
2508
2509 StringRef FieldName = Field->getName();
2510
2511 // Ignore unnamed fields.
2512 if (FieldName.empty())
2513 continue;
2514
2515 // Get the location for the field.
2516 llvm::DIFile *FieldDefUnit = getOrCreateFile(Field->getLocation());
2517 unsigned FieldLine = getLineNumber(Field->getLocation());
2518 QualType FType = Field->getType();
2519 uint64_t FieldSize = 0;
2520 uint32_t FieldAlign = 0;
2521
2522 if (!FType->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
2523
2524 // Bit size, align and offset of the type.
2525 FieldSize = Field->isBitField()
2526 ? Field->getBitWidthValue(CGM.getContext())
2527 : CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(FType);
2528 FieldAlign = getTypeAlignIfRequired(FType, CGM.getContext());
2529 }
2530
2531 uint64_t FieldOffset;
2532 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isNonFragile()) {
2533 // We don't know the runtime offset of an ivar if we're using the
2534 // non-fragile ABI. For bitfields, use the bit offset into the first
2535 // byte of storage of the bitfield. For other fields, use zero.
2536 if (Field->isBitField()) {
2537 FieldOffset =
2538 CGM.getObjCRuntime().ComputeBitfieldBitOffset(CGM, ID, Field);
2539 FieldOffset %= CGM.getContext().getCharWidth();
2540 } else {
2541 FieldOffset = 0;
2542 }
2543 } else {
2544 FieldOffset = RL.getFieldOffset(FieldNo);
2545 }
2546
2547 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
2548 if (Field->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Protected)
2549 Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagProtected;
2550 else if (Field->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Private)
2551 Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagPrivate;
2552 else if (Field->getAccessControl() == ObjCIvarDecl::Public)
2553 Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagPublic;
2554
2555 llvm::MDNode *PropertyNode = nullptr;
2556 if (ObjCImplementationDecl *ImpD = ID->getImplementation()) {
2557 if (ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PImpD =
2558 ImpD->FindPropertyImplIvarDecl(Field->getIdentifier())) {
2559 if (ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PImpD->getPropertyDecl()) {
2560 SourceLocation Loc = PD->getLocation();
2561 llvm::DIFile *PUnit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
2562 unsigned PLine = getLineNumber(Loc);
2563 ObjCMethodDecl *Getter = PD->getGetterMethodDecl();
2564 ObjCMethodDecl *Setter = PD->getSetterMethodDecl();
2565 PropertyNode = DBuilder.createObjCProperty(
2566 PD->getName(), PUnit, PLine,
2567 hasDefaultGetterName(PD, Getter)
2568 ? ""
2569 : getSelectorName(PD->getGetterName()),
2570 hasDefaultSetterName(PD, Setter)
2571 ? ""
2572 : getSelectorName(PD->getSetterName()),
2573 PD->getPropertyAttributes(),
2574 getOrCreateType(PD->getType(), PUnit));
2575 }
2576 }
2577 }
2578 FieldTy = DBuilder.createObjCIVar(FieldName, FieldDefUnit, FieldLine,
2579 FieldSize, FieldAlign, FieldOffset, Flags,
2580 FieldTy, PropertyNode);
2581 EltTys.push_back(FieldTy);
2582 }
2583
2584 llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
2585 DBuilder.replaceArrays(RealDecl, Elements);
2586
2587 LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
2588 return RealDecl;
2589}

2591llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const VectorType *Ty,
2592 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2593 llvm::DIType *ElementTy = getOrCreateType(Ty->getElementType(), Unit);
2594 int64_t Count = Ty->getNumElements();
2595
2596 llvm::Metadata *Subscript;
2597 QualType QTy(Ty, 0);
2598 auto SizeExpr = SizeExprCache.find(QTy);
2599 if (SizeExpr != SizeExprCache.end())
2600 Subscript = DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(0, SizeExpr->getSecond());
2601 else
2602 Subscript = DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(0, Count ? Count : -1);
2603 llvm::DINodeArray SubscriptArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Subscript);
2604
2605 uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
2606 auto Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
2607
2608 return DBuilder.createVectorType(Size, Align, ElementTy, SubscriptArray);
2609}
2610
2611llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const ArrayType *Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2612 uint64_t Size;
2613 uint32_t Align;
2614
2615 // FIXME: make getTypeAlign() aware of VLAs and incomplete array types
2616 if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(Ty)) {
2617 Size = 0;
2618 Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(CGM.getContext().getBaseElementType(VAT),
2619 CGM.getContext());
2620 } else if (Ty->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
2621 Size = 0;
2622 if (Ty->getElementType()->isIncompleteType())
2623 Align = 0;
2624 else
2625 Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty->getElementType(), CGM.getContext());
2626 } else if (Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
2627 Size = 0;
2628 Align = 0;
2629 } else {
2630 // Size and align of the whole array, not the element type.
2631 Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
2632 Align = getTypeAlignIfRequired(Ty, CGM.getContext());
2633 }
2634
2635 // Add the dimensions of the array. FIXME: This loses CV qualifiers from
2636 // interior arrays, do we care? Why aren't nested arrays represented the
2637 // obvious/recursive way?
2638 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> Subscripts;
2639 QualType EltTy(Ty, 0);
2640 while ((Ty = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(EltTy))) {
2641 // If the number of elements is known, then count is that number. Otherwise,
2642 // it's -1. This allows us to represent a subrange with an array of 0
2643 // elements, like this:
2644 //
2645 // struct foo {
2646 // int x[0];
2647 // };
2648 int64_t Count = -1; // Count == -1 is an unbounded array.
2649 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(Ty))
2650 Count = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
2651 else if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(Ty)) {
2652 if (Expr *Size = VAT->getSizeExpr()) {
2653 Expr::EvalResult Result;
2654 if (Size->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGM.getContext()))
2655 Count = Result.Val.getInt().getExtValue();
2656 }
2657 }
2658
2659 auto SizeNode = SizeExprCache.find(EltTy);
2660 if (SizeNode != SizeExprCache.end())
2661 Subscripts.push_back(
2662 DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(0, SizeNode->getSecond()));
2663 else
2664 Subscripts.push_back(DBuilder.getOrCreateSubrange(0, Count));
2665 EltTy = Ty->getElementType();
2666 }
2667
2668 llvm::DINodeArray SubscriptArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Subscripts);
2669
2670 return DBuilder.createArrayType(Size, Align, getOrCreateType(EltTy, Unit),
2671 SubscriptArray);
2672}

2686llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateType(const MemberPointerType *Ty,
2687 llvm::DIFile *U) {
2688 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
2689 uint64_t Size = 0;
2690
2691 if (!Ty->isIncompleteType()) {
2692 Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
2693
2694 // Set the MS inheritance model. There is no flag for the unspecified model.
2695 if (CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
2696 switch (Ty->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl()->getMSInheritanceModel()) {
2697 case MSInheritanceAttr::Keyword_single_inheritance:
2698 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagSingleInheritance;
2699 break;
2700 case MSInheritanceAttr::Keyword_multiple_inheritance:
2701 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagMultipleInheritance;
2702 break;
2703 case MSInheritanceAttr::Keyword_virtual_inheritance:
2704 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagVirtualInheritance;
2705 break;
2706 case MSInheritanceAttr::Keyword_unspecified_inheritance:
2707 break;
2708 }
2709 }
2710 }
2711
2712 llvm::DIType *ClassType = getOrCreateType(QualType(Ty->getClass(), 0), U);
2713 if (Ty->isMemberDataPointerType())
2714 return DBuilder.createMemberPointerType(
2715 getOrCreateType(Ty->getPointeeType(), U), ClassType, Size, /*Align=*/0,
2716 Flags);
2717
2718 const FunctionProtoType *FPT =
2719 Ty->getPointeeType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2720 return DBuilder.createMemberPointerType(
2721 getOrCreateInstanceMethodType(
2722 CXXMethodDecl::getThisType(FPT, Ty->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl()),
2723 FPT, U),
2724 ClassType, Size, /*Align=*/0, Flags);
2725}

2736llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateEnumType(const EnumType *Ty) {
2737 const EnumDecl *ED = Ty->getDecl();
2738
2739 uint64_t Size = 0;
2740 uint32_t Align = 0;
2741 if (!ED->getTypeForDecl()->isIncompleteType()) {
2742 Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(ED->getTypeForDecl());
2743 Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(ED, CGM.getContext());
2744 }
2745
2746 SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
2747
2748 bool isImportedFromModule =
2749 DebugTypeExtRefs && ED->isFromASTFile() && ED->getDefinition();
2750
2751 // If this is just a forward declaration, construct an appropriately
2752 // marked node and just return it.
2753 if (isImportedFromModule || !ED->getDefinition()) {
2754 // Note that it is possible for enums to be created as part of
2755 // their own declcontext. In this case a FwdDecl will be created
2756 // twice. This doesn't cause a problem because both FwdDecls are
2757 // entered into the ReplaceMap: finalize() will replace the first
2758 // FwdDecl with the second and then replace the second with
2759 // complete type.
2760 llvm::DIScope *EDContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(ED);
2761 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ED->getLocation());
2762 llvm::TempDIScope TmpContext(DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
2763 llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type, "", TheCU, DefUnit, 0));
2764
2765 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ED->getLocation());
2766 StringRef EDName = ED->getName();
2767 llvm::DIType *RetTy = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
2768 llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type, EDName, EDContext, DefUnit, Line,
2769 0, Size, Align, llvm::DINode::FlagFwdDecl, Identifier);
2770
2771 ReplaceMap.emplace_back(
2772 std::piecewise_construct, std::make_tuple(Ty),
2773 std::make_tuple(static_cast<llvm::Metadata *>(RetTy)));
2774 return RetTy;
2775 }
2776
2777 return CreateTypeDefinition(Ty);
2778}

2780llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeDefinition(const EnumType *Ty) {
2781 const EnumDecl *ED = Ty->getDecl();
2782 uint64_t Size = 0;
2783 uint32_t Align = 0;
2784 if (!ED->getTypeForDecl()->isIncompleteType()) {
2785 Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(ED->getTypeForDecl());
2786 Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(ED, CGM.getContext());
2787 }
2788
2789 SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
2790
2791 // Create elements for each enumerator.
2792 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> Enumerators;
2793 ED = ED->getDefinition();
2794 bool IsSigned = ED->getIntegerType()->isSignedIntegerType();
2795 for (const auto *Enum : ED->enumerators()) {
2796 const auto &InitVal = Enum->getInitVal();
2797 auto Value = IsSigned ? InitVal.getSExtValue() : InitVal.getZExtValue();
2798 Enumerators.push_back(
2799 DBuilder.createEnumerator(Enum->getName(), Value, !IsSigned));
2800 }
2801
2802 // Return a CompositeType for the enum itself.
2803 llvm::DINodeArray EltArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(Enumerators);
2804
2805 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(ED->getLocation());
2806 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(ED->getLocation());
2807 llvm::DIScope *EnumContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(ED);
2808 llvm::DIType *ClassTy = getOrCreateType(ED->getIntegerType(), DefUnit);
2809 return DBuilder.createEnumerationType(EnumContext, ED->getName(), DefUnit,
2810 Line, Size, Align, EltArray, ClassTy,
2811 Identifier, ED->isScoped());
2812}

2828
2829static QualType UnwrapTypeForDebugInfo(QualType T, const ASTContext &C) {
2830 Qualifiers Quals;
2831 do {
2832 Qualifiers InnerQuals = T.getLocalQualifiers();
2833 // Qualifiers::operator+() doesn't like it if you add a Qualifier
2834 // that is already there.
2835 Quals += Qualifiers::removeCommonQualifiers(Quals, InnerQuals);
2836 Quals += InnerQuals;
2837 QualType LastT = T;
2838 switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
2839 default:
2840 return C.getQualifiedType(T.getTypePtr(), Quals);
2841 case Type::TemplateSpecialization: {
2842 const auto *Spec = cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(T);
2843 if (Spec->isTypeAlias())
2844 return C.getQualifiedType(T.getTypePtr(), Quals);
2845 T = Spec->desugar();
2846 break;
2847 }
2848 case Type::TypeOfExpr:
2849 T = cast<TypeOfExprType>(T)->getUnderlyingExpr()->getType();
2850 break;
2851 case Type::TypeOf:
2852 T = cast<TypeOfType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
2853 break;
2854 case Type::Decltype:
2855 T = cast<DecltypeType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
2856 break;
2857 case Type::UnaryTransform:
2858 T = cast<UnaryTransformType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
2859 break;
2860 case Type::Attributed:
2861 T = cast<AttributedType>(T)->getEquivalentType();
2862 break;
2863 case Type::Elaborated:
2864 T = cast<ElaboratedType>(T)->getNamedType();
2865 break;
2866 case Type::Paren:
2867 T = cast<ParenType>(T)->getInnerType();
2868 break;
2869 case Type::MacroQualified:
2870 T = cast<MacroQualifiedType>(T)->getUnderlyingType();
2871 break;
2872 case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParm:
2873 T = cast<SubstTemplateTypeParmType>(T)->getReplacementType();
2874 break;
2875 case Type::Auto:
2876 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization: {
2877 QualType DT = cast<DeducedType>(T)->getDeducedType();
2878 assert(!DT.isNull() && "Undeduced types shouldn't reach here.");
2879 T = DT;
2880 break;
2881 }
2882 case Type::Adjusted:
2883 case Type::Decayed:
2884 // Decayed and adjusted types use the adjusted type in LLVM and DWARF.
2885 T = cast<AdjustedType>(T)->getAdjustedType();
2886 break;
2887 }
2888
2889 assert(T != LastT && "Type unwrapping failed to unwrap!");
2890 (void)LastT;
2891 } while (true);
2892}
2893
2894llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getTypeOrNull(QualType Ty) {
2895
2896 // Unwrap the type as needed for debug information.
2897 Ty = UnwrapTypeForDebugInfo(Ty, CGM.getContext());
2898
2899 auto It = TypeCache.find(Ty.getAsOpaquePtr());
2900 if (It != TypeCache.end()) {
2901 // Verify that the debug info still exists.
2902 if (llvm::Metadata *V = It->second)
2903 return cast<llvm::DIType>(V);
2904 }
2905
2906 return nullptr;
2907}

2909void CGDebugInfo::completeTemplateDefinition(
2910 const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl &SD) {
2911 if (DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
2912 return;
2913 completeUnusedClass(SD);
2914}
2915
2916void CGDebugInfo::completeUnusedClass(const CXXRecordDecl &D) {
2917 if (DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
2918 return;
2919
2920 completeClassData(&D);
2921 // In case this type has no member function definitions being emitted, ensure
2922 // it is retained
2923 RetainedTypes.push_back(CGM.getContext().getRecordType(&D).getAsOpaquePtr());
2924}
2925
2926llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateType(QualType Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2927 if (Ty.isNull())
2928 return nullptr;
2929
2930 // Unwrap the type as needed for debug information.
2931 Ty = UnwrapTypeForDebugInfo(Ty, CGM.getContext());
2932
2933 if (auto *T = getTypeOrNull(Ty))
2934 return T;
2935
2936 llvm::DIType *Res = CreateTypeNode(Ty, Unit);
2937 void *TyPtr = Ty.getAsOpaquePtr();
2938
2939 // And update the type cache.
2940 TypeCache[TyPtr].reset(Res);
2941
2942 return Res;
2943}
2944
2945llvm::DIModule *CGDebugInfo::getParentModuleOrNull(const Decl *D) {
2946 // A forward declaration inside a module header does not belong to the module.
2947 if (isa<RecordDecl>(D) && !cast<RecordDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
2948 return nullptr;
2949 if (DebugTypeExtRefs && D->isFromASTFile()) {
2950 // Record a reference to an imported clang module or precompiled header.
2951 auto *Reader = CGM.getContext().getExternalSource();
2952 auto Idx = D->getOwningModuleID();
2953 auto Info = Reader->getSourceDescriptor(Idx);
2954 if (Info)
2955 return getOrCreateModuleRef(*Info, /*SkeletonCU=*/true);
2956 } else if (ClangModuleMap) {
2957 // We are building a clang module or a precompiled header.
2958 //
2959 // TODO: When D is a CXXRecordDecl or a C++ Enum, the ODR applies
2960 // and it wouldn't be necessary to specify the parent scope
2961 // because the type is already unique by definition (it would look
2962 // like the output of -fno-standalone-debug). On the other hand,
2963 // the parent scope helps a consumer to quickly locate the object
2964 // file where the type's definition is located, so it might be
2965 // best to make this behavior a command line or debugger tuning
2966 // option.
2967 if (Module *M = D->getOwningModule()) {
2968 // This is a (sub-)module.
2969 auto Info = ExternalASTSource::ASTSourceDescriptor(*M);
2970 return getOrCreateModuleRef(Info, /*SkeletonCU=*/false);
2971 } else {
2972 // This the precompiled header being built.
2973 return getOrCreateModuleRef(PCHDescriptor, /*SkeletonCU=*/false);
2974 }
2975 }
2976
2977 return nullptr;
2978}

2980llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateTypeNode(QualType Ty, llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
2981 // Handle qualifiers, which recursively handles what they refer to.
2982 if (Ty.hasLocalQualifiers())
2983 return CreateQualifiedType(Ty, Unit);
2984
2985 // Work out details of type.
2986 switch (Ty->getTypeClass()) {
2987#define TYPE(Class, Base)
2988#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
2989#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base)
2990#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
2991#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
2992 llvm_unreachable("Dependent types cannot show up in debug information");
2993
2994 case Type::ExtVector:
2995 case Type::Vector:
2996 return CreateType(cast<VectorType>(Ty), Unit);
2997 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
2998 return CreateType(cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(Ty), Unit);
2999 case Type::ObjCObject:
3000 return CreateType(cast<ObjCObjectType>(Ty), Unit);
3001 case Type::ObjCTypeParam:
3002 return CreateType(cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(Ty), Unit);
3003 case Type::ObjCInterface:
3004 return CreateType(cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(Ty), Unit);
3005 case Type::Builtin:
3006 return CreateType(cast<BuiltinType>(Ty));
3007 case Type::Complex:
3008 return CreateType(cast<ComplexType>(Ty));
3009 case Type::Pointer:
3010 return CreateType(cast<PointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3011 case Type::BlockPointer:
3012 return CreateType(cast<BlockPointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3013 case Type::Typedef:
3014 return CreateType(cast<TypedefType>(Ty), Unit);
3015 case Type::Record:
3016 return CreateType(cast<RecordType>(Ty));
3017 case Type::Enum:
3018 return CreateEnumType(cast<EnumType>(Ty));
3019 case Type::FunctionProto:
3020 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3021 return CreateType(cast<FunctionType>(Ty), Unit);
3022 case Type::ConstantArray:
3023 case Type::VariableArray:
3024 case Type::IncompleteArray:
3025 return CreateType(cast<ArrayType>(Ty), Unit);
3026
3027 case Type::LValueReference:
3028 return CreateType(cast<LValueReferenceType>(Ty), Unit);
3029 case Type::RValueReference:
3030 return CreateType(cast<RValueReferenceType>(Ty), Unit);
3031
3032 case Type::MemberPointer:
3033 return CreateType(cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty), Unit);
3034
3035 case Type::Atomic:
3036 return CreateType(cast<AtomicType>(Ty), Unit);
3037
3038 case Type::Pipe:
3039 return CreateType(cast<PipeType>(Ty), Unit);
3040

3049 case Type::Elaborated:

3061 llvm_unreachable("type should have been unwrapped!");

3064llvm::DICompositeType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateLimitedType(const RecordType *Ty,
3065 llvm::DIFile *Unit) {
3066 QualType QTy(Ty, 0);
3067
3068 auto *T = cast_or_null<llvm::DICompositeType>(getTypeOrNull(QTy));
3069
3070 // We may have cached a forward decl when we could have created
3071 // a non-forward decl. Go ahead and create a non-forward decl
3072 // now.
3073 if (T && !T->isForwardDecl())
3074 return T;
3075
3076 // Otherwise create the type.
3077 llvm::DICompositeType *Res = CreateLimitedType(Ty);
3078
3079 // Propagate members from the declaration to the definition
3080 // CreateType(const RecordType*) will overwrite this with the members in the
3081 // correct order if the full type is needed.
3082 DBuilder.replaceArrays(Res, T ? T->getElements() : llvm::DINodeArray());
3083
3084 // And update the type cache.
3085 TypeCache[QTy.getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(Res);
3086 return Res;
3087}
3088
3089// TODO: Currently used for context chains when limiting debug info.
3090llvm::DICompositeType *CGDebugInfo::CreateLimitedType(const RecordType *Ty) {
3091 RecordDecl *RD = Ty->getDecl();
3092
3093 // Get overall information about the record type for the debug info.
3094 llvm::DIFile *DefUnit = getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation());
3095 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(RD->getLocation());
3096 StringRef RDName = getClassName(RD);
3097
3098 llvm::DIScope *RDContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(RD);
3099
3100 // If we ended up creating the type during the context chain construction,
3101 // just return that.
3102 auto *T = cast_or_null<llvm::DICompositeType>(
3103 getTypeOrNull(CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD)));
3104 if (T && (!T->isForwardDecl() || !RD->getDefinition()))
3105 return T;
3106
3107 // If this is just a forward or incomplete declaration, construct an
3108 // appropriately marked node and just return it.
3109 const RecordDecl *D = RD->getDefinition();
3110 if (!D || !D->isCompleteDefinition())
3111 return getOrCreateRecordFwdDecl(Ty, RDContext);
3112
3113 uint64_t Size = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
3114 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(D, CGM.getContext());
3115
3116 SmallString<256> Identifier = getTypeIdentifier(Ty, CGM, TheCU);
3117
3118 // Explicitly record the calling convention for C++ records.
3119 auto Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3120 if (auto CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
3121 if (CGM.getCXXABI().getRecordArgABI(CXXRD) == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect)
3122 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagTypePassByReference;
3123 else
3124 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagTypePassByValue;
3125
3126 // Record if a C++ record is non-trivial type.
3127 if (!CXXRD->isTrivial())
3128 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagNonTrivial;
3129 }
3130
3131 llvm::DICompositeType *RealDecl = DBuilder.createReplaceableCompositeType(
3132 getTagForRecord(RD), RDName, RDContext, DefUnit, Line, 0, Size, Align,
3133 Flags, Identifier);
3134
3135 // Elements of composite types usually have back to the type, creating
3136 // uniquing cycles. Distinct nodes are more efficient.
3137 switch (RealDecl->getTag()) {
3138 default:
3139 llvm_unreachable("invalid composite type tag");
3140
3141 case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_array_type:
3142 case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_enumeration_type:
3143 // Array elements and most enumeration elements don't have back references,
3144 // so they don't tend to be involved in uniquing cycles and there is some
3145 // chance of merging them when linking together two modules. Only make
3146 // them distinct if they are ODR-uniqued.
3147 if (Identifier.empty())
3148 break;
3149 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3150
3151 case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_structure_type:
3152 case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_union_type:
3153 case llvm::dwarf::DW_TAG_class_type:
3154 // Immediately resolve to a distinct node.
3155 RealDecl =
3156 llvm::MDNode::replaceWithDistinct(llvm::TempDICompositeType(RealDecl));
3157 break;
3158 }
3159
3160 RegionMap[Ty->getDecl()].reset(RealDecl);
3161 TypeCache[QualType(Ty, 0).getAsOpaquePtr()].reset(RealDecl);
3162
3163 if (const auto *TSpecial = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
3164 DBuilder.replaceArrays(RealDecl, llvm::DINodeArray(),
3165 CollectCXXTemplateParams(TSpecial, DefUnit));
3166 return RealDecl;
3167}
3168
3169void CGDebugInfo::CollectContainingType(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
3170 llvm::DICompositeType *RealDecl) {
3171 // A class's primary base or the class itself contains the vtable.
3172 llvm::DICompositeType *ContainingType = nullptr;
3173 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3174 if (const CXXRecordDecl *PBase = RL.getPrimaryBase()) {
3175 // Seek non-virtual primary base root.
3176 while (1) {
3177 const ASTRecordLayout &BRL = CGM.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(PBase);
3178 const CXXRecordDecl *PBT = BRL.getPrimaryBase();
3179 if (PBT && !BRL.isPrimaryBaseVirtual())
3180 PBase = PBT;
3181 else
3182 break;
3183 }
3184 ContainingType = cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(
3185 getOrCreateType(QualType(PBase->getTypeForDecl(), 0),
3186 getOrCreateFile(RD->getLocation())));
3187 } else if (RD->isDynamicClass())
3188 ContainingType = RealDecl;
3189
3190 DBuilder.replaceVTableHolder(RealDecl, ContainingType);
3191}

3205void CGDebugInfo::collectFunctionDeclProps(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
3206 StringRef &Name,
3207 StringRef &LinkageName,
3208 llvm::DIScope *&FDContext,
3209 llvm::DINodeArray &TParamsArray,
3210 llvm::DINode::DIFlags &Flags) {
3211 const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3212 Name = getFunctionName(FD);
3213 // Use mangled name as linkage name for C/C++ functions.
3214 if (FD->hasPrototype()) {
3215 LinkageName = CGM.getMangledName(GD);
3216 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
3217 }
3218 // No need to replicate the linkage name if it isn't different from the
3219 // subprogram name, no need to have it at all unless coverage is enabled or
3220 // debug is set to more than just line tables or extra debug info is needed.
3221 if (LinkageName == Name || (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitGcovArcs &&
3222 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitGcovNotes &&
3223 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DebugInfoForProfiling &&
3224 DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly))
3225 LinkageName = StringRef();
3226
3227 if (DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo) {
3228 if (const NamespaceDecl *NSDecl =
3229 dyn_cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(FD->getDeclContext()))
3230 FDContext = getOrCreateNamespace(NSDecl);
3231 else if (const RecordDecl *RDecl =
3232 dyn_cast_or_null<RecordDecl>(FD->getDeclContext())) {
3233 llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(RDecl);
3234 FDContext = getContextDescriptor(RDecl, Mod ? Mod : TheCU);
3235 }
3236 // Check if it is a noreturn-marked function
3237 if (FD->isNoReturn())
3238 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagNoReturn;
3239 // Collect template parameters.
3240 TParamsArray = CollectFunctionTemplateParams(FD, Unit);
3241 }
3242}

3244void CGDebugInfo::collectVarDeclProps(const VarDecl *VD, llvm::DIFile *&Unit,
3245 unsigned &LineNo, QualType &T,
3246 StringRef &Name, StringRef &LinkageName,
3247 llvm::MDTuple *&TemplateParameters,
3248 llvm::DIScope *&VDContext) {
3249 Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
3250 LineNo = getLineNumber(VD->getLocation());
3251
3252 setLocation(VD->getLocation());
3253
3254 T = VD->getType();
3255 if (T->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
3256 // CodeGen turns int[] into int[1] so we'll do the same here.
3257 llvm::APInt ConstVal(32, 1);
3258 QualType ET = CGM.getContext().getAsArrayType(T)->getElementType();
3259
3260 T = CGM.getContext().getConstantArrayType(ET, ConstVal, ArrayType::Normal,
3261 0);
3262 }
3263
3264 Name = VD->getName();
3265 if (VD->getDeclContext() && !isa<FunctionDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()) &&
3266 !isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()))
3267 LinkageName = CGM.getMangledName(VD);
3268 if (LinkageName == Name)
3269 LinkageName = StringRef();
3270
3271 if (isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD)) {
3272 llvm::DINodeArray parameterNodes = CollectVarTemplateParams(VD, &*Unit);
3273 TemplateParameters = parameterNodes.get();
3274 } else {
3275 TemplateParameters = nullptr;
3276 }
3277
3278 // Since we emit declarations (DW_AT_members) for static members, place the
3279 // definition of those static members in the namespace they were declared in
3280 // in the source code (the lexical decl context).
3281 // FIXME: Generalize this for even non-member global variables where the
3282 // declaration and definition may have different lexical decl contexts, once
3283 // we have support for emitting declarations of (non-member) global variables.
3284 const DeclContext *DC = VD->isStaticDataMember() ? VD->getLexicalDeclContext()
3285 : VD->getDeclContext();
3286 // When a record type contains an in-line initialization of a static data
3287 // member, and the record type is marked as __declspec(dllexport), an implicit
3288 // definition of the member will be created in the record context. DWARF
3289 // doesn't seem to have a nice way to describe this in a form that consumers
3290 // are likely to understand, so fake the "normal" situation of a definition
3291 // outside the class by putting it in the global scope.
3292 if (DC->isRecord())
3293 DC = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
3294
3295 llvm::DIScope *Mod = getParentModuleOrNull(VD);
3296 VDContext = getContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(DC), Mod ? Mod : TheCU);
3297}

3300 bool Stub) {

3302 StringRef Name, LinkageName;
3303 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;

3310 Flags);

3325

3333 }

3338 TParamsArray.get(), getFunctionDeclaration(FD));

3341 std::make_tuple(CanonDecl),

3344}

3377llvm::DINode *CGDebugInfo::getDeclarationOrDefinition(const Decl *D) {
3378 // We only need a declaration (not a definition) of the type - so use whatever
3379 // we would otherwise do to get a type for a pointee. (forward declarations in
3380 // limited debug info, full definitions (if the type definition is available)
3381 // in unlimited debug info)
3382 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypeDecl>(D))
3383 return getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getTypeDeclType(TD),
3384 getOrCreateFile(TD->getLocation()));
3385 auto I = DeclCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
3386
3387 if (I != DeclCache.end()) {
3388 auto N = I->second;
3389 if (auto *GVE = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression>(N))
3390 return GVE->getVariable();
3391 return dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DINode>(N);
3392 }
3393
3394 // No definition for now. Emit a forward definition that might be
3395 // merged with a potential upcoming definition.
3396 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
3397 return getFunctionForwardDeclaration(FD);
3398 else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
3399 return getGlobalVariableForwardDeclaration(VD);
3400
3401 return nullptr;
3402}
3403
3404llvm::DISubprogram *CGDebugInfo::getFunctionDeclaration(const Decl *D) {
3405 if (!D || DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
3406 return nullptr;
3407
3408 const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D);
3409 if (!FD)
3410 return nullptr;
3411
3412 // Setup context.
3413 auto *S = getDeclContextDescriptor(D);
3414
3415 auto MI = SPCache.find(FD->getCanonicalDecl());
3416 if (MI == SPCache.end()) {
3417 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD->getCanonicalDecl())) {
3418 return CreateCXXMemberFunction(MD, getOrCreateFile(MD->getLocation()),
3419 cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(S));
3420 }
3421 }
3422 if (MI != SPCache.end()) {
3423 auto *SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(MI->second);
3424 if (SP && !SP->isDefinition())
3425 return SP;
3426 }
3427
3428 for (auto NextFD : FD->redecls()) {
3429 auto MI = SPCache.find(NextFD->getCanonicalDecl());
3430 if (MI != SPCache.end()) {
3431 auto *SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(MI->second);
3432 if (SP && !SP->isDefinition())
3433 return SP;
3434 }
3435 }
3436 return nullptr;
3437}
3438
3439// getOrCreateFunctionType - Construct type. If it is a c++ method, include
3440// implicit parameter "this".
3441llvm::DISubroutineType *CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateFunctionType(const Decl *D,
3442 QualType FnType,
3443 llvm::DIFile *F) {
3444 if (!D || DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
3445 // Create fake but valid subroutine type. Otherwise -verify would fail, and
3446 // subprogram DIE will miss DW_AT_decl_file and DW_AT_decl_line fields.
3447 return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(None));
3448
3449 if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D))
3450 return getOrCreateMethodType(Method, F);
3451
3452 const auto *FTy = FnType->getAs<FunctionType>();
3453 CallingConv CC = FTy ? FTy->getCallConv() : CallingConv::CC_C;
3454
3455 if (const auto *OMethod = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
3456 // Add "self" and "_cmd"
3457 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> Elts;
3458
3459 // First element is always return type. For 'void' functions it is NULL.
3460 QualType ResultTy = OMethod->getReturnType();
3461
3462 // Replace the instancetype keyword with the actual type.
3463 if (ResultTy == CGM.getContext().getObjCInstanceType())
3464 ResultTy = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(
3465 QualType(OMethod->getClassInterface()->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
3466
3467 Elts.push_back(getOrCreateType(ResultTy, F));
3468 // "self" pointer is always first argument.
3469 QualType SelfDeclTy;
3470 if (auto *SelfDecl = OMethod->getSelfDecl())
3471 SelfDeclTy = SelfDecl->getType();
3472 else if (auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType))
3473 if (FPT->getNumParams() > 1)
3474 SelfDeclTy = FPT->getParamType(0);
3475 if (!SelfDeclTy.isNull())
3476 Elts.push_back(
3477 CreateSelfType(SelfDeclTy, getOrCreateType(SelfDeclTy, F)));
3478 // "_cmd" pointer is always second argument.
3479 Elts.push_back(DBuilder.createArtificialType(
3480 getOrCreateType(CGM.getContext().getObjCSelType(), F)));
3481 // Get rest of the arguments.
3482 for (const auto *PI : OMethod->parameters())
3483 Elts.push_back(getOrCreateType(PI->getType(), F));
3484 // Variadic methods need a special marker at the end of the type list.
3485 if (OMethod->isVariadic())
3486 Elts.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
3487
3488 llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(Elts);
3489 return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, llvm::DINode::FlagZero,
3490 getDwarfCC(CC));
3491 }
3492
3493 // Handle variadic function types; they need an additional
3494 // unspecified parameter.
3495 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
3496 if (FD->isVariadic()) {
3497 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
3498 EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(FD->getReturnType(), F));
3499 if (const auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FnType))
3500 for (QualType ParamType : FPT->param_types())
3501 EltTys.push_back(getOrCreateType(ParamType, F));
3502 EltTys.push_back(DBuilder.createUnspecifiedParameter());
3503 llvm::DITypeRefArray EltTypeArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateTypeArray(EltTys);
3504 return DBuilder.createSubroutineType(EltTypeArray, llvm::DINode::FlagZero,
3505 getDwarfCC(CC));
3506 }
3507
3508 return cast<llvm::DISubroutineType>(getOrCreateType(FnType, F));
3509}

3511void CGDebugInfo::EmitFunctionStart(GlobalDecl GD, SourceLocation Loc,
3512 SourceLocation ScopeLoc, QualType FnType,
3513 llvm::Function *Fn, bool CurFuncIsThunk,
3514 CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
3515
3516 StringRef Name;
3517 StringRef LinkageName;
3518
3519 FnBeginRegionCount.push_back(LexicalBlockStack.size());
3520
3521 const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
3522 bool HasDecl = (D != nullptr);
3523
3524 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3525 llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
3526 llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
3527 llvm::DIScope *FDContext = Unit;
3528 llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray;
3529 if (!HasDecl) {
3530 // Use llvm function name.
3531 LinkageName = Fn->getName();
3532 } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3533 // If there is a subprogram for this function available then use it.
3534 auto FI = SPCache.find(FD->getCanonicalDecl());
3535 if (FI != SPCache.end()) {
3536 auto *SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(FI->second);
3537 if (SP && SP->isDefinition()) {
3538 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(SP);
3539 RegionMap[D].reset(SP);
3540 return;
3541 }
3542 }
3543 collectFunctionDeclProps(GD, Unit, Name, LinkageName, FDContext,
3544 TParamsArray, Flags);
3545 } else if (const auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
3546 Name = getObjCMethodName(OMD);
3547 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
3548 } else if (isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
3549 GD.getDynamicInitKind() != DynamicInitKind::NoStub) {
3550 // This is a global initializer or atexit destructor for a global variable.
3551 Name = getDynamicInitializerName(cast<VarDecl>(D), GD.getDynamicInitKind(),
3552 Fn);
3553 } else {
3554 // Use llvm function name.
3555 Name = Fn->getName();
3556 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
3557 }
3558 if (Name.startswith("\01"))
3559 Name = Name.substr(1);
3560
3561 if (!HasDecl || D->isImplicit() || D->hasAttr<ArtificialAttr>()) {
3562 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
3563 // Artificial functions should not silently reuse CurLoc.
3564 CurLoc = SourceLocation();
3565 }
3566
3567 if (CurFuncIsThunk)
3568 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagThunk;
3569
3570 if (Fn->hasLocalLinkage())
3571 SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagLocalToUnit;
3572 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
3573 SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
3574
3575 llvm::DINode::DIFlags FlagsForDef = Flags | getCallSiteRelatedAttrs();
3576 llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlagsForDef =
3577 SPFlags | llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagDefinition;
3578
3579 unsigned LineNo = getLineNumber(Loc);
3580 unsigned ScopeLine = getLineNumber(ScopeLoc);
3581
3582 // FIXME: The function declaration we're constructing here is mostly reusing
3583 // declarations from CXXMethodDecl and not constructing new ones for arbitrary
3584 // FunctionDecls. When/if we fix this we can have FDContext be TheCU/null for
3585 // all subprograms instead of the actual context since subprogram definitions
3586 // are emitted as CU level entities by the backend.
3587 llvm::DISubprogram *SP = DBuilder.createFunction(
3588 FDContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo,
3589 getOrCreateFunctionType(D, FnType, Unit), ScopeLine, FlagsForDef,
3590 SPFlagsForDef, TParamsArray.get(), getFunctionDeclaration(D));
3591 Fn->setSubprogram(SP);
3592 // We might get here with a VarDecl in the case we're generating
3593 // code for the initialization of globals. Do not record these decls
3594 // as they will overwrite the actual VarDecl Decl in the cache.
3595 if (HasDecl && isa<FunctionDecl>(D))
3596 DeclCache[D->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(SP);
3597
3598 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion >= 5) {
3599 // Starting with DWARF V5 method declarations are emitted as children of
3600 // the interface type.
3601 if (const auto *OMD = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
3602 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = OMD->getClassInterface();
3603 QualType QTy(ID->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
3604 auto It = TypeCache.find(QTy.getAsOpaquePtr());
3605 if (It != TypeCache.end()) {
3606 llvm::DICompositeType *InterfaceDecl =
3607 cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(It->second);
3608 llvm::DISubprogram *FD = DBuilder.createFunction(
3609 InterfaceDecl, Name, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo,
3610 getOrCreateFunctionType(D, FnType, Unit), ScopeLine, Flags, SPFlags,
3611 TParamsArray.get());
3612 DBuilder.finalizeSubprogram(FD);
3613 ObjCMethodCache[ID].push_back(FD);
3614 }
3615 }
3616 }
3617
3618 // Push the function onto the lexical block stack.
3619 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(SP);
3620
3621 if (HasDecl)
3622 RegionMap[D].reset(SP);
3623}
3624
3625void CGDebugInfo::EmitFunctionDecl(GlobalDecl GD, SourceLocation Loc,
3626 QualType FnType) {
3627 StringRef Name;
3628 StringRef LinkageName;
3629
3630 const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
3631 if (!D)
3632 return;
3633
3634 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3635 llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(Loc);
3636 llvm::DIScope *FDContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(D);
3637 llvm::DINodeArray TParamsArray;
3638 if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
3639 // If there is a DISubprogram for this function available then use it.
3640 collectFunctionDeclProps(GD, Unit, Name, LinkageName, FDContext,
3641 TParamsArray, Flags);
3642 } else if (const auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D)) {
3643 Name = getObjCMethodName(OMD);
3644 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped;
3645 } else {
3646 llvm_unreachable("not a function or ObjC method");
3647 }
3648 if (!Name.empty() && Name[0] == '\01')
3649 Name = Name.substr(1);
3650
3651 if (D->isImplicit()) {
3652 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
3653 // Artificial functions without a location should not silently reuse CurLoc.
3654 if (Loc.isInvalid())
3655 CurLoc = SourceLocation();
3656 }
3657 unsigned LineNo = getLineNumber(Loc);
3658 unsigned ScopeLine = 0;
3659 llvm::DISubprogram::DISPFlags SPFlags = llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagZero;
3660 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize)
3661 SPFlags |= llvm::DISubprogram::SPFlagOptimized;
3662
3663 DBuilder.retainType(DBuilder.createFunction(
3664 FDContext, Name, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo,
3665 getOrCreateFunctionType(D, FnType, Unit), ScopeLine, Flags, SPFlags,
3666 TParamsArray.get(), getFunctionDeclaration(D)));
3667}
3668
3669void CGDebugInfo::EmitInlineFunctionStart(CGBuilderTy &Builder, GlobalDecl GD) {
3670 const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
3671 // If there is a subprogram for this function available then use it.
3672 auto FI = SPCache.find(FD->getCanonicalDecl());
3673 llvm::DISubprogram *SP = nullptr;
3674 if (FI != SPCache.end())
3675 SP = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DISubprogram>(FI->second);
3676 if (!SP || !SP->isDefinition())
3677 SP = getFunctionStub(GD);
3678 FnBeginRegionCount.push_back(LexicalBlockStack.size());
3679 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(SP);
3680 setInlinedAt(Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
3681 EmitLocation(Builder, FD->getLocation());
3682}
3683
3684void CGDebugInfo::EmitInlineFunctionEnd(CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
3685 assert(CurInlinedAt && "unbalanced inline scope stack");
3686 EmitFunctionEnd(Builder, nullptr);
3687 setInlinedAt(llvm::DebugLoc(CurInlinedAt).getInlinedAt());
3688}
3689
3690void CGDebugInfo::EmitLocation(CGBuilderTy &Builder, SourceLocation Loc) {
3691 // Update our current location
3692 setLocation(Loc);
3693
3694 if (CurLoc.isInvalid() || CurLoc.isMacroID() || LexicalBlockStack.empty())
3695 return;
3696
3697 llvm::MDNode *Scope = LexicalBlockStack.back();
3698 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(llvm::DebugLoc::get(
3699 getLineNumber(CurLoc), getColumnNumber(CurLoc), Scope, CurInlinedAt));
3700}
3701
3702void CGDebugInfo::CreateLexicalBlock(SourceLocation Loc) {
3703 llvm::MDNode *Back = nullptr;
3704 if (!LexicalBlockStack.empty())
3705 Back = LexicalBlockStack.back().get();
3706 LexicalBlockStack.emplace_back(DBuilder.createLexicalBlock(
3707 cast<llvm::DIScope>(Back), getOrCreateFile(CurLoc), getLineNumber(CurLoc),
3708 getColumnNumber(CurLoc)));
3709}
3710
3711void CGDebugInfo::AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(
3712 unsigned AddressSpace, SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &Expr) const {
3713 Optional<unsigned> DWARFAddressSpace =
3714 CGM.getTarget().getDWARFAddressSpace(AddressSpace);
3715 if (!DWARFAddressSpace)
3716 return;
3717
3718 Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_constu);
3719 Expr.push_back(DWARFAddressSpace.getValue());
3720 Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_swap);
3721 Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_xderef);
3722}
3723
3724void CGDebugInfo::EmitLexicalBlockStart(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
3725 SourceLocation Loc) {
3726 // Set our current location.
3727 setLocation(Loc);
3728
3729 // Emit a line table change for the current location inside the new scope.
3730 Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(
3731 llvm::DebugLoc::get(getLineNumber(Loc), getColumnNumber(Loc),
3732 LexicalBlockStack.back(), CurInlinedAt));
3733
3734 if (DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
3735 return;
3736
3737 // Create a new lexical block and push it on the stack.
3738 CreateLexicalBlock(Loc);
3739}
3740
3741void CGDebugInfo::EmitLexicalBlockEnd(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
3742 SourceLocation Loc) {
3743 assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
3744
3745 // Provide an entry in the line table for the end of the block.
3746 EmitLocation(Builder, Loc);
3747
3748 if (DebugKind <= codegenoptions::DebugLineTablesOnly)
3749 return;
3750
3751 LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
3752}
3753
3754void CGDebugInfo::EmitFunctionEnd(CGBuilderTy &Builder, llvm::Function *Fn) {
3755 assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
3756 unsigned RCount = FnBeginRegionCount.back();
3757 assert(RCount <= LexicalBlockStack.size() && "Region stack mismatch");
3758
3759 // Pop all regions for this function.
3760 while (LexicalBlockStack.size() != RCount) {
3761 // Provide an entry in the line table for the end of the block.
3762 EmitLocation(Builder, CurLoc);
3763 LexicalBlockStack.pop_back();
3764 }
3765 FnBeginRegionCount.pop_back();
3766
3767 if (Fn && Fn->getSubprogram())
3768 DBuilder.finalizeSubprogram(Fn->getSubprogram());
3769}
3770
3771CGDebugInfo::BlockByRefType
3772CGDebugInfo::EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(const VarDecl *VD,
3773 uint64_t *XOffset) {
3774 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 5> EltTys;
3775 QualType FType;
3776 uint64_t FieldSize, FieldOffset;
3777 uint32_t FieldAlign;
3778
3779 llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
3780 QualType Type = VD->getType();
3781
3782 FieldOffset = 0;
3783 FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
3784 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__isa", &FieldOffset));
3785 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__forwarding", &FieldOffset));
3786 FType = CGM.getContext().IntTy;
3787 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__flags", &FieldOffset));
3788 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__size", &FieldOffset));
3789
3790 bool HasCopyAndDispose = CGM.getContext().BlockRequiresCopying(Type, VD);
3791 if (HasCopyAndDispose) {
3792 FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
3793 EltTys.push_back(
3794 CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__copy_helper", &FieldOffset));
3795 EltTys.push_back(
3796 CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__destroy_helper", &FieldOffset));
3797 }
3798 bool HasByrefExtendedLayout;
3799 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime;
3800 if (CGM.getContext().getByrefLifetime(Type, Lifetime,
3801 HasByrefExtendedLayout) &&
3802 HasByrefExtendedLayout) {
3803 FType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(CGM.getContext().VoidTy);
3804 EltTys.push_back(
3805 CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "__byref_variable_layout", &FieldOffset));
3806 }
3807
3808 CharUnits Align = CGM.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
3809 if (Align > CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
3810 CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(0))) {
3811 CharUnits FieldOffsetInBytes =
3812 CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(FieldOffset);
3813 CharUnits AlignedOffsetInBytes = FieldOffsetInBytes.alignTo(Align);
3814 CharUnits NumPaddingBytes = AlignedOffsetInBytes - FieldOffsetInBytes;
3815
3816 if (NumPaddingBytes.isPositive()) {
3817 llvm::APInt pad(32, NumPaddingBytes.getQuantity());
3818 FType = CGM.getContext().getConstantArrayType(CGM.getContext().CharTy,
3819 pad, ArrayType::Normal, 0);
3820 EltTys.push_back(CreateMemberType(Unit, FType, "", &FieldOffset));
3821 }
3822 }
3823
3824 FType = Type;
3825 llvm::DIType *WrappedTy = getOrCreateType(FType, Unit);
3826 FieldSize = CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(FType);
3827 FieldAlign = CGM.getContext().toBits(Align);
3828
3829 *XOffset = FieldOffset;
3830 llvm::DIType *FieldTy = DBuilder.createMemberType(
3831 Unit, VD->getName(), Unit, 0, FieldSize, FieldAlign, FieldOffset,
3832 llvm::DINode::FlagZero, WrappedTy);
3833 EltTys.push_back(FieldTy);
3834 FieldOffset += FieldSize;
3835
3836 llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
3837 return {DBuilder.createStructType(Unit, "", Unit, 0, FieldOffset, 0,
3838 llvm::DINode::FlagZero, nullptr, Elements),
3839 WrappedTy};
3840}
3841
3842llvm::DILocalVariable *CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclare(const VarDecl *VD,
3843 llvm::Value *Storage,
3844 llvm::Optional<unsigned> ArgNo,
3845 CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
3846 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
3847 assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
3848 if (VD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
3849 return nullptr;
3850
3851 bool Unwritten =
3852 VD->isImplicit() || (isa<Decl>(VD->getDeclContext()) &&
3853 cast<Decl>(VD->getDeclContext())->isImplicit());
3854 llvm::DIFile *Unit = nullptr;
3855 if (!Unwritten)
3856 Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
3857 llvm::DIType *Ty;
3858 uint64_t XOffset = 0;
3859 if (VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>())
3860 Ty = EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(VD, &XOffset).WrappedType;
3861 else
3862 Ty = getOrCreateType(VD->getType(), Unit);
3863
3864 // If there is no debug info for this type then do not emit debug info
3865 // for this variable.
3866 if (!Ty)
3867 return nullptr;
3868
3869 // Get location information.
3870 unsigned Line = 0;
3871 unsigned Column = 0;
3872 if (!Unwritten) {
3873 Line = getLineNumber(VD->getLocation());
3874 Column = getColumnNumber(VD->getLocation());
3875 }
3876 SmallVector<int64_t, 13> Expr;
3877 llvm::DINode::DIFlags Flags = llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
3878 if (VD->isImplicit())
3879 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
3880
3881 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
3882
3883 unsigned AddressSpace = CGM.getAddressSpaceForType(VD->getType());
3884 AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(AddressSpace, Expr);
3885
3886 // If this is implicit parameter of CXXThis or ObjCSelf kind, then give it an
3887 // object pointer flag.
3888 if (const auto *IPD = dyn_cast<ImplicitParamDecl>(VD)) {
3889 if (IPD->getParameterKind() == ImplicitParamDecl::CXXThis ||
3890 IPD->getParameterKind() == ImplicitParamDecl::ObjCSelf)
3891 Flags |= llvm::DINode::FlagObjectPointer;
3892 }
3893
3894 // Note: Older versions of clang used to emit byval references with an extra
3895 // DW_OP_deref, because they referenced the IR arg directly instead of
3896 // referencing an alloca. Newer versions of LLVM don't treat allocas
3897 // differently from other function arguments when used in a dbg.declare.
3898 auto *Scope = cast<llvm::DIScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
3899 StringRef Name = VD->getName();
3900 if (!Name.empty()) {
3901 if (VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>()) {
3902 // Here, we need an offset *into* the alloca.
3903 CharUnits offset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(32);
3904 Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
3905 // offset of __forwarding field
3906 offset = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(
3907 CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(0));
3908 Expr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
3909 Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
3910 Expr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
3911 // offset of x field
3912 offset = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(XOffset);
3913 Expr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
3914 }
3915 } else if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(VD->getType())) {
3916 // If VD is an anonymous union then Storage represents value for
3917 // all union fields.
3918 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
3919 if (RD->isUnion() && RD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion()) {
3920 // GDB has trouble finding local variables in anonymous unions, so we emit
3921 // artificial local variables for each of the members.
3922 //
3923 // FIXME: Remove this code as soon as GDB supports this.
3924 // The debug info verifier in LLVM operates based on the assumption that a
3925 // variable has the same size as its storage and we had to disable the
3926 // check for artificial variables.
3927 for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
3928 llvm::DIType *FieldTy = getOrCreateType(Field->getType(), Unit);
3929 StringRef FieldName = Field->getName();
3930
3931 // Ignore unnamed fields. Do not ignore unnamed records.
3932 if (FieldName.empty() && !isa<RecordType>(Field->getType()))
3933 continue;
3934
3935 // Use VarDecl's Tag, Scope and Line number.
3936 auto FieldAlign = getDeclAlignIfRequired(Field, CGM.getContext());
3937 auto *D = DBuilder.createAutoVariable(
3938 Scope, FieldName, Unit, Line, FieldTy, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize,
3939 Flags | llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial, FieldAlign);
3940
3941 // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
3942 DBuilder.insertDeclare(
3943 Storage, D, DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
3944 llvm::DebugLoc::get(Line, Column, Scope, CurInlinedAt),
3945 Builder.GetInsertBlock());
3946 }
3947 }
3948 }
3949
3950 // Create the descriptor for the variable.
3951 auto *D = ArgNo ? DBuilder.createParameterVariable(
3952 Scope, Name, *ArgNo, Unit, Line, Ty,
3953 CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize, Flags)
3954 : DBuilder.createAutoVariable(Scope, Name, Unit, Line, Ty,
3955 CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize,
3956 Flags, Align);
3957
3958 // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
3959 DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
3960 llvm::DebugLoc::get(Line, Column, Scope, CurInlinedAt),
3961 Builder.GetInsertBlock());
3962
3963 return D;
3964}
3965
3966llvm::DILocalVariable *
3967CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfAutoVariable(const VarDecl *VD, llvm::Value *Storage,
3968 CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
3969 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
3970 return EmitDeclare(VD, Storage, llvm::None, Builder);
3971}

3973void CGDebugInfo::EmitLabel(const LabelDecl *D, CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
3974 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
3975 assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
3976
3977 if (D->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
3978 return;
3979
3980 auto *Scope = cast<llvm::DIScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
3981 llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(D->getLocation());
3982
3983 // Get location information.
3984 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(D->getLocation());
3985 unsigned Column = getColumnNumber(D->getLocation());
3986
3987 StringRef Name = D->getName();
3988
3989 // Create the descriptor for the label.
3990 auto *L =
3991 DBuilder.createLabel(Scope, Name, Unit, Line, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize);
3992
3993 // Insert an llvm.dbg.label into the current block.
3994 DBuilder.insertLabel(L,
3995 llvm::DebugLoc::get(Line, Column, Scope, CurInlinedAt),
3996 Builder.GetInsertBlock());
3997}

3999llvm::DIType *CGDebugInfo::CreateSelfType(const QualType &QualTy,
4000 llvm::DIType *Ty) {
4001 llvm::DIType *CachedTy = getTypeOrNull(QualTy);
4002 if (CachedTy)
4003 Ty = CachedTy;
4004 return DBuilder.createObjectPointerType(Ty);
4005}
4006
4007void CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfBlockDeclRefVariable(
4008 const VarDecl *VD, llvm::Value *Storage, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4009 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo, llvm::Instruction *InsertPoint) {
4010 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
4011 assert(!LexicalBlockStack.empty() && "Region stack mismatch, stack empty!");
4012
4013 if (Builder.GetInsertBlock() == nullptr)
4014 return;
4015 if (VD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
4016 return;
4017
4018 bool isByRef = VD->hasAttr<BlocksAttr>();
4019
4020 uint64_t XOffset = 0;
4021 llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
4022 llvm::DIType *Ty;
4023 if (isByRef)
4024 Ty = EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(VD, &XOffset).WrappedType;
4025 else
4026 Ty = getOrCreateType(VD->getType(), Unit);
4027
4028 // Self is passed along as an implicit non-arg variable in a
4029 // block. Mark it as the object pointer.
4030 if (const auto *IPD = dyn_cast<ImplicitParamDecl>(VD))
4031 if (IPD->getParameterKind() == ImplicitParamDecl::ObjCSelf)
4032 Ty = CreateSelfType(VD->getType(), Ty);
4033
4034 // Get location information.
4035 unsigned Line = getLineNumber(VD->getLocation());
4036 unsigned Column = getColumnNumber(VD->getLocation());
4037
4038 const llvm::DataLayout &target = CGM.getDataLayout();
4039
4040 CharUnits offset = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
4041 target.getStructLayout(blockInfo.StructureType)
4042 ->getElementOffset(blockInfo.getCapture(VD).getIndex()));
4043
4044 SmallVector<int64_t, 9> addr;
4045 addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
4046 addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
4047 addr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
4048 if (isByRef) {
4049 addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
4050 addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
4051 // offset of __forwarding field
4052 offset =
4053 CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(target.getPointerSizeInBits(0));
4054 addr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
4055 addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_deref);
4056 addr.push_back(llvm::dwarf::DW_OP_plus_uconst);
4057 // offset of x field
4058 offset = CGM.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(XOffset);
4059 addr.push_back(offset.getQuantity());
4060 }
4061
4062 // Create the descriptor for the variable.
4063 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
4064 auto *D = DBuilder.createAutoVariable(
4065 cast<llvm::DILocalScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back()), VD->getName(), Unit,
4066 Line, Ty, false, llvm::DINode::FlagZero, Align);
4067
4068 // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
4069 auto DL =
4070 llvm::DebugLoc::get(Line, Column, LexicalBlockStack.back(), CurInlinedAt);
4071 auto *Expr = DBuilder.createExpression(addr);
4072 if (InsertPoint)
4073 DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, Expr, DL, InsertPoint);
4074 else
4075 DBuilder.insertDeclare(Storage, D, Expr, DL, Builder.GetInsertBlock());
4076}

4078void CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfArgVariable(const VarDecl *VD, llvm::Value *AI,
4079 unsigned ArgNo,
4080 CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
4081 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
4082 EmitDeclare(VD, AI, ArgNo, Builder);
4083}

4085namespace {
4086struct BlockLayoutChunk {
4087 uint64_t OffsetInBits;
4088 const BlockDecl::Capture *Capture;
4089};
4090bool operator<(const BlockLayoutChunk &l, const BlockLayoutChunk &r) {
4091 return l.OffsetInBits < r.OffsetInBits;
4092}
4093} // namespace
4094
4095void CGDebugInfo::collectDefaultFieldsForBlockLiteralDeclare(
4096 const CGBlockInfo &Block, const ASTContext &Context, SourceLocation Loc,
4097 const llvm::StructLayout &BlockLayout, llvm::DIFile *Unit,
4098 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Metadata *> &Fields) {
4099 // Blocks in OpenCL have unique constraints which make the standard fields
4100 // redundant while requiring size and align fields for enqueue_kernel. See
4101 // initializeForBlockHeader in CGBlocks.cpp
4102 if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4103 Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__size", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
4104 BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(0),
4105 Unit, Unit));
4106 Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__align", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
4107 BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(1),
4108 Unit, Unit));
4109 } else {
4110 Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__isa", Context.VoidPtrTy, Loc, AS_public,
4111 BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(0),
4112 Unit, Unit));
4113 Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__flags", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
4114 BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(1),
4115 Unit, Unit));
4116 Fields.push_back(
4117 createFieldType("__reserved", Context.IntTy, Loc, AS_public,
4118 BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(2), Unit, Unit));
4119 auto *FnTy = Block.getBlockExpr()->getFunctionType();
4120 auto FnPtrType = CGM.getContext().getPointerType(FnTy->desugar());
4121 Fields.push_back(createFieldType("__FuncPtr", FnPtrType, Loc, AS_public,
4122 BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(3),
4123 Unit, Unit));
4124 Fields.push_back(createFieldType(
4125 "__descriptor",
4126 Context.getPointerType(Block.NeedsCopyDispose
4127 ? Context.getBlockDescriptorExtendedType()
4128 : Context.getBlockDescriptorType()),
4129 Loc, AS_public, BlockLayout.getElementOffsetInBits(4), Unit, Unit));
4130 }
4131}
4132
4133void CGDebugInfo::EmitDeclareOfBlockLiteralArgVariable(const CGBlockInfo &block,
4134 StringRef Name,
4135 unsigned ArgNo,
4136 llvm::AllocaInst *Alloca,
4137 CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
4138 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
4139 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
4140 const BlockDecl *blockDecl = block.getBlockDecl();
4141
4142 // Collect some general information about the block's location.
4143 SourceLocation loc = blockDecl->getCaretLocation();
4144 llvm::DIFile *tunit = getOrCreateFile(loc);
4145 unsigned line = getLineNumber(loc);
4146 unsigned column = getColumnNumber(loc);
4147
4148 // Build the debug-info type for the block literal.
4149 getDeclContextDescriptor(blockDecl);
4150
4151 const llvm::StructLayout *blockLayout =
4152 CGM.getDataLayout().getStructLayout(block.StructureType);
4153
4154 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> fields;
4155 collectDefaultFieldsForBlockLiteralDeclare(block, C, loc, *blockLayout, tunit,
4156 fields);
4157
4158 // We want to sort the captures by offset, not because DWARF
4159 // requires this, but because we're paranoid about debuggers.
4160 SmallVector<BlockLayoutChunk, 8> chunks;
4161
4162 // 'this' capture.
4163 if (blockDecl->capturesCXXThis()) {
4164 BlockLayoutChunk chunk;
4165 chunk.OffsetInBits =
4166 blockLayout->getElementOffsetInBits(block.CXXThisIndex);
4167 chunk.Capture = nullptr;
4168 chunks.push_back(chunk);
4169 }
4170
4171 // Variable captures.
4172 for (const auto &capture : blockDecl->captures()) {
4173 const VarDecl *variable = capture.getVariable();
4174 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &captureInfo = block.getCapture(variable);
4175
4176 // Ignore constant captures.
4177 if (captureInfo.isConstant())
4178 continue;
4179
4180 BlockLayoutChunk chunk;
4181 chunk.OffsetInBits =
4182 blockLayout->getElementOffsetInBits(captureInfo.getIndex());
4183 chunk.Capture = &capture;
4184 chunks.push_back(chunk);
4185 }
4186
4187 // Sort by offset.
4188 llvm::array_pod_sort(chunks.begin(), chunks.end());
4189
4190 for (const BlockLayoutChunk &Chunk : chunks) {
4191 uint64_t offsetInBits = Chunk.OffsetInBits;
4192 const BlockDecl::Capture *capture = Chunk.Capture;
4193
4194 // If we have a null capture, this must be the C++ 'this' capture.
4195 if (!capture) {
4196 QualType type;
4197 if (auto *Method =
4198 cast_or_null<CXXMethodDecl>(blockDecl->getNonClosureContext()))
4199 type = Method->getThisType();
4200 else if (auto *RDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(blockDecl->getParent()))
4201 type = QualType(RDecl->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
4202 else
4203 llvm_unreachable("unexpected block declcontext");
4204
4205 fields.push_back(createFieldType("this", type, loc, AS_public,
4206 offsetInBits, tunit, tunit));
4207 continue;
4208 }
4209
4210 const VarDecl *variable = capture->getVariable();
4211 StringRef name = variable->getName();
4212
4213 llvm::DIType *fieldType;
4214 if (capture->isByRef()) {
4215 TypeInfo PtrInfo = C.getTypeInfo(C.VoidPtrTy);
4216 auto Align = PtrInfo.AlignIsRequired ? PtrInfo.Align : 0;
4217 // FIXME: This recomputes the layout of the BlockByRefWrapper.
4218 uint64_t xoffset;
4219 fieldType =
4220 EmitTypeForVarWithBlocksAttr(variable, &xoffset).BlockByRefWrapper;
4221 fieldType = DBuilder.createPointerType(fieldType, PtrInfo.Width);
4222 fieldType = DBuilder.createMemberType(tunit, name, tunit, line,
4223 PtrInfo.Width, Align, offsetInBits,
4224 llvm::DINode::FlagZero, fieldType);
4225 } else {
4226 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(variable, CGM.getContext());
4227 fieldType = createFieldType(name, variable->getType(), loc, AS_public,
4228 offsetInBits, Align, tunit, tunit);
4229 }
4230 fields.push_back(fieldType);
4231 }
4232
4233 SmallString<36> typeName;
4234 llvm::raw_svector_ostream(typeName)
4235 << "__block_literal_" << CGM.getUniqueBlockCount();
4236
4237 llvm::DINodeArray fieldsArray = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(fields);
4238
4239 llvm::DIType *type =
4240 DBuilder.createStructType(tunit, typeName.str(), tunit, line,
4241 CGM.getContext().toBits(block.BlockSize), 0,
4242 llvm::DINode::FlagZero, nullptr, fieldsArray);
4243 type = DBuilder.createPointerType(type, CGM.PointerWidthInBits);
4244
4245 // Get overall information about the block.
4246 llvm::DINode::DIFlags flags = llvm::DINode::FlagArtificial;
4247 auto *scope = cast<llvm::DILocalScope>(LexicalBlockStack.back());
4248
4249 // Create the descriptor for the parameter.
4250 auto *debugVar = DBuilder.createParameterVariable(
4251 scope, Name, ArgNo, tunit, line, type, CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize, flags);
4252
4253 // Insert an llvm.dbg.declare into the current block.
4254 DBuilder.insertDeclare(Alloca, debugVar, DBuilder.createExpression(),
4255 llvm::DebugLoc::get(line, column, scope, CurInlinedAt),
4256 Builder.GetInsertBlock());
4257}

4259llvm::DIDerivedType *
4260CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateStaticDataMemberDeclarationOrNull(const VarDecl *D) {
4261 if (!D || !D->isStaticDataMember())
4262 return nullptr;
4263
4264 auto MI = StaticDataMemberCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
4265 if (MI != StaticDataMemberCache.end()) {
4266 assert(MI->second && "Static data member declaration should still exist");
4267 return MI->second;
4268 }
4269
4270 // If the member wasn't found in the cache, lazily construct and add it to the
4271 // type (used when a limited form of the type is emitted).
4272 auto DC = D->getDeclContext();
4273 auto *Ctxt = cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(getDeclContextDescriptor(D));
4274 return CreateRecordStaticField(D, Ctxt, cast<RecordDecl>(DC));
4275}

4277llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *CGDebugInfo::CollectAnonRecordDecls(
4278 const RecordDecl *RD, llvm::DIFile *Unit, unsigned LineNo,
4279 StringRef LinkageName, llvm::GlobalVariable *Var, llvm::DIScope *DContext) {
4280 llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *GVE = nullptr;
4281
4282 for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
4283 llvm::DIType *FieldTy = getOrCreateType(Field->getType(), Unit);
4284 StringRef FieldName = Field->getName();
4285
4286 // Ignore unnamed fields, but recurse into anonymous records.
4287 if (FieldName.empty()) {
4288 if (const auto *RT = dyn_cast<RecordType>(Field->getType()))
4289 GVE = CollectAnonRecordDecls(RT->getDecl(), Unit, LineNo, LinkageName,
4290 Var, DContext);
4291 continue;
4292 }
4293 // Use VarDecl's Tag, Scope and Line number.
4294 GVE = DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
4295 DContext, FieldName, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo, FieldTy,
4296 Var->hasLocalLinkage());
4297 Var->addDebugInfo(GVE);
4298 }
4299 return GVE;
4300}
4301
4302void CGDebugInfo::EmitGlobalVariable(llvm::GlobalVariable *Var,
4303 const VarDecl *D) {
4304 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
4305 if (D->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
4306 return;
4307
4308 // If we already created a DIGlobalVariable for this declaration, just attach
4309 // it to the llvm::GlobalVariable.
4310 auto Cached = DeclCache.find(D->getCanonicalDecl());
4311 if (Cached != DeclCache.end())
4312 return Var->addDebugInfo(
4313 cast<llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression>(Cached->second));
4314
4315 // Create global variable debug descriptor.
4316 llvm::DIFile *Unit = nullptr;
4317 llvm::DIScope *DContext = nullptr;
4318 unsigned LineNo;
4319 StringRef DeclName, LinkageName;
4320 QualType T;
4321 llvm::MDTuple *TemplateParameters = nullptr;
4322 collectVarDeclProps(D, Unit, LineNo, T, DeclName, LinkageName,
4323 TemplateParameters, DContext);
4324
4325 // Attempt to store one global variable for the declaration - even if we
4326 // emit a lot of fields.
4327 llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression *GVE = nullptr;
4328
4329 // If this is an anonymous union then we'll want to emit a global
4330 // variable for each member of the anonymous union so that it's possible
4331 // to find the name of any field in the union.
4332 if (T->isUnionType() && DeclName.empty()) {
4333 const RecordDecl *RD = T->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
4334 assert(RD->isAnonymousStructOrUnion() &&
4335 "unnamed non-anonymous struct or union?");
4336 GVE = CollectAnonRecordDecls(RD, Unit, LineNo, LinkageName, Var, DContext);
4337 } else {
4338 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(D, CGM.getContext());
4339
4340 SmallVector<int64_t, 4> Expr;
4341 unsigned AddressSpace = CGM.getAddressSpaceForType(D->getType());
4342 if (CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
4343 if (D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>())
4344 AddressSpace =
4345 CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_shared);
4346 else if (D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>())
4347 AddressSpace =
4348 CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_constant);
4349 }
4350 AppendAddressSpaceXDeref(AddressSpace, Expr);
4351
4352 GVE = DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
4353 DContext, DeclName, LinkageName, Unit, LineNo, getOrCreateType(T, Unit),
4354 Var->hasLocalLinkage(),
4355 Expr.empty() ? nullptr : DBuilder.createExpression(Expr),
4356 getOrCreateStaticDataMemberDeclarationOrNull(D), TemplateParameters,
4357 Align);
4358 Var->addDebugInfo(GVE);
4359 }
4360 DeclCache[D->getCanonicalDecl()].reset(GVE);
4361}
