4363void CGDebugInfo::EmitGlobalVariable(const ValueDecl *VD, const APValue &Init) {
4364 assert(DebugKind >= codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo);
4365 if (VD->hasAttr<NoDebugAttr>())
4366 return;
4367 auto Align = getDeclAlignIfRequired(VD, CGM.getContext());
4368 // Create the descriptor for the variable.
4369 llvm::DIFile *Unit = getOrCreateFile(VD->getLocation());
4370 StringRef Name = VD->getName();
4371 llvm::DIType *Ty = getOrCreateType(VD->getType(), Unit);
4372
4373 // Do not use global variables for enums, unless for CodeView.
4374 if (const auto *ECD = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(VD)) {
4375 const auto *ED = cast<EnumDecl>(ECD->getDeclContext());
4376 assert(isa<EnumType>(ED->getTypeForDecl()) && "Enum without EnumType?");
4377 (void)ED;
4378
4379 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)
4380 return;
4381 }
4382
4383 llvm::DIScope *DContext = nullptr;
4384
4385 // Do not emit separate definitions for function local consts.
4386 if (isa<FunctionDecl>(VD->getDeclContext()))
4387 return;
4388
4389 // Emit definition for static members in CodeView.
4390 VD = cast<ValueDecl>(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
4391 auto *VarD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(VD);
4392 if (VarD && VarD->isStaticDataMember()) {
4393 auto *RD = cast<RecordDecl>(VarD->getDeclContext());
4394 getDeclContextDescriptor(VarD);
4395 // Ensure that the type is retained even though it's otherwise unreferenced.
4396 //
4397 // FIXME: This is probably unnecessary, since Ty should reference RD
4398 // through its scope.
4399 RetainedTypes.push_back(
4400 CGM.getContext().getRecordType(RD).getAsOpaquePtr());
4401
4402 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitCodeView)
4403 return;
4404
4405 // Use the global scope for static members.
4406 DContext = getContextDescriptor(
4407 cast<Decl>(CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl()), TheCU);
4408 } else {
4409 DContext = getDeclContextDescriptor(VD);
4410 }
4411
4412 auto &GV = DeclCache[VD];
4413 if (GV)
4414 return;
4415 llvm::DIExpression *InitExpr = nullptr;
4416 if (CGM.getContext().getTypeSize(VD->getType()) <= 64) {
4417 // FIXME: Add a representation for integer constants wider than 64 bits.
4418 if (Init.isInt())
4419 InitExpr =
4420 DBuilder.createConstantValueExpression(Init.getInt().getExtValue());
4421 else if (Init.isFloat())
4422 InitExpr = DBuilder.createConstantValueExpression(
4423 Init.getFloat().bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue());
4424 }
4425
4426 llvm::MDTuple *TemplateParameters = nullptr;
4427
4428 if (isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD))
4429 if (VarD) {
4430 llvm::DINodeArray parameterNodes = CollectVarTemplateParams(VarD, &*Unit);
4431 TemplateParameters = parameterNodes.get();
4432 }
4433
4434 GV.reset(DBuilder.createGlobalVariableExpression(
4435 DContext, Name, StringRef(), Unit, getLineNumber(VD->getLocation()), Ty,
4436 true, InitExpr, getOrCreateStaticDataMemberDeclarationOrNull(VarD),
4437 TemplateParameters, Align));
4438}

4460void CGDebugInfo::EmitUsingDecl(const UsingDecl &UD) {
4461 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() < codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo)
4462 return;
4463 assert(UD.shadow_size() &&
4464 "We shouldn't be codegening an invalid UsingDecl containing no decls");
4465 // Emitting one decl is sufficient - debuggers can detect that this is an
4466 // overloaded name & provide lookup for all the overloads.
4467 const UsingShadowDecl &USD = **UD.shadow_begin();
4468
4469 // FIXME: Skip functions with undeduced auto return type for now since we
4470 // don't currently have the plumbing for separate declarations & definitions
4471 // of free functions and mismatched types (auto in the declaration, concrete
4472 // return type in the definition)
4473 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(USD.getUnderlyingDecl()))
4474 if (const auto *AT =
4475 FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getContainedAutoType())
4476 if (AT->getDeducedType().isNull())
4477 return;
4478 if (llvm::DINode *Target =
4479 getDeclarationOrDefinition(USD.getUnderlyingDecl())) {
4480 auto Loc = USD.getLocation();
4481 DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
4482 getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(USD.getDeclContext())), Target,
4483 getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc));
4484 }
4485}

4500llvm::DIImportedEntity *
4501CGDebugInfo::EmitNamespaceAlias(const NamespaceAliasDecl &NA) {
4502 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() < codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo)
4503 return nullptr;
4504 auto &VH = NamespaceAliasCache[&NA];
4505 if (VH)
4506 return cast<llvm::DIImportedEntity>(VH);
4507 llvm::DIImportedEntity *R;
4508 auto Loc = NA.getLocation();
4509 if (const auto *Underlying =
4510 dyn_cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(NA.getAliasedNamespace()))
4511 // This could cache & dedup here rather than relying on metadata deduping.
4512 R = DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
4513 getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(NA.getDeclContext())),
4514 EmitNamespaceAlias(*Underlying), getOrCreateFile(Loc),
4515 getLineNumber(Loc), NA.getName());
4516 else
4517 R = DBuilder.createImportedDeclaration(
4518 getCurrentContextDescriptor(cast<Decl>(NA.getDeclContext())),
4519 getOrCreateNamespace(cast<NamespaceDecl>(NA.getAliasedNamespace())),
4520 getOrCreateFile(Loc), getLineNumber(Loc), NA.getName());
4521 VH.reset(R);
4522 return R;
4523}

4525llvm::DINamespace *
4526CGDebugInfo::getOrCreateNamespace(const NamespaceDecl *NSDecl) {
4527 // Don't canonicalize the NamespaceDecl here: The DINamespace will be uniqued
4528 // if necessary, and this way multiple declarations of the same namespace in
4529 // different parent modules stay distinct.
4530 auto I = NamespaceCache.find(NSDecl);
4531 if (I != NamespaceCache.end())
4532 return cast<llvm::DINamespace>(I->second);
4533
4534 llvm::DIScope *Context = getDeclContextDescriptor(NSDecl);
4535 // Don't trust the context if it is a DIModule (see comment above).
4536 llvm::DINamespace *NS =
4537 DBuilder.createNameSpace(Context, NSDecl->getName(), NSDecl->isInline());
4538 NamespaceCache[NSDecl].reset(NS);
4539 return NS;
4540}

4546
4547void CGDebugInfo::finalize() {
4548 // Creating types might create further types - invalidating the current
4549 // element and the size(), so don't cache/reference them.
4550 for (size_t i = 0; i != ObjCInterfaceCache.size(); ++i) {
4551 ObjCInterfaceCacheEntry E = ObjCInterfaceCache[i];
4552 llvm::DIType *Ty = E.Type->getDecl()->getDefinition()
4553 ? CreateTypeDefinition(E.Type, E.Unit)
4554 : E.Decl;
4555 DBuilder.replaceTemporary(llvm::TempDIType(E.Decl), Ty);
4556 }
4557
4558 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion >= 5) {
4559 // Add methods to interface.
4560 for (const auto &P : ObjCMethodCache) {
4561 if (P.second.empty())
4562 continue;
4563
4564 QualType QTy(P.first->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
4565 auto It = TypeCache.find(QTy.getAsOpaquePtr());
4566 assert(It != TypeCache.end());
4567
4568 llvm::DICompositeType *InterfaceDecl =
4569 cast<llvm::DICompositeType>(It->second);
4570
4571 SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 16> EltTys;
4572 auto CurrenetElts = InterfaceDecl->getElements();
4573 EltTys.append(CurrenetElts.begin(), CurrenetElts.end());
4574 for (auto &MD : P.second)
4575 EltTys.push_back(MD);
4576 llvm::DINodeArray Elements = DBuilder.getOrCreateArray(EltTys);
4577 DBuilder.replaceArrays(InterfaceDecl, Elements);
4578 }
4579 }
4580
4581 for (const auto &P : ReplaceMap) {
4582 assert(P.second);
4583 auto *Ty = cast<llvm::DIType>(P.second);
4584 assert(Ty->isForwardDecl());
4585
4586 auto It = TypeCache.find(P.first);
4587 assert(It != TypeCache.end());
4588 assert(It->second);
4589
4590 DBuilder.replaceTemporary(llvm::TempDIType(Ty),
4591 cast<llvm::DIType>(It->second));
4592 }
4593
4594 for (const auto &P : FwdDeclReplaceMap) {
4595 assert(P.second);
4596 llvm::TempMDNode FwdDecl(cast<llvm::MDNode>(P.second));
4597 llvm::Metadata *Repl;
4598
4599 auto It = DeclCache.find(P.first);
4600 // If there has been no definition for the declaration, call RAUW
4601 // with ourselves, that will destroy the temporary MDNode and
4602 // replace it with a standard one, avoiding leaking memory.
4603 if (It == DeclCache.end())
4604 Repl = P.second;
4605 else
4606 Repl = It->second;
4607
4608 if (auto *GVE = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::DIGlobalVariableExpression>(Repl))
4609 Repl = GVE->getVariable();
4610 DBuilder.replaceTemporary(std::move(FwdDecl), cast<llvm::MDNode>(Repl));
4611 }
4612
4613 // We keep our own list of retained types, because we need to look
4614 // up the final type in the type cache.
4615 for (auto &RT : RetainedTypes)
4616 if (auto MD = TypeCache[RT])
4617 DBuilder.retainType(cast<llvm::DIType>(MD));
4618
4619 DBuilder.finalize();
4620}

4639llvm::DINode::DIFlags CGDebugInfo::getCallSiteRelatedAttrs() const {
4640 // Call site-related attributes are only useful in optimized programs, and
4641 // when there's a possibility of debugging backtraces.
4642 if (!CGM.getLangOpts().Optimize || DebugKind == codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo ||
4643 DebugKind == codegenoptions::LocTrackingOnly)
4644 return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
4645
4646 // Call site-related attributes are available in DWARF v5. Some debuggers,
4647 // while not fully DWARF v5-compliant, may accept these attributes as if they
4648 // were part of DWARF v4.
4649 bool SupportsDWARFv4Ext =
4650 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion == 4 &&
4651 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebuggerTuning() == llvm::DebuggerKind::LLDB;
4652 if (!SupportsDWARFv4Ext && CGM.getCodeGenOpts().DwarfVersion < 5)
4653 return llvm::DINode::FlagZero;
4654
4655 return llvm::DINode::FlagAllCallsDescribed;
4656}
